{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EU9XZF132c9LPkF5g3ZEMm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# CLOCHE\n     2→\n     3→A system for grow-coding high quality applications.\n     4→\n     5→# What is it\n     6→\n     7→Cloche provides \n     8→- containerized environments for coding agents to operate in isolation\n     9→- a workflow syntax for linking Agentic and Script-driven task nodes\n    10→- a focus on creating validated code\n    11→- self-evolving tooling that grows with your codebase in response to encountered errors\n    12→\n    13→## Installation\n    14→\n    15→See [docs/INSTALL.md](docs/INSTALL.md) for full installation instructions\n    16→covering build from source, `go install`, and other methods.\n    17→\n    18→## Containers\n    19→\n    20→Coding agents are powerful, but running them interactively turns the human into the bottleneck.\n    21→\n    22→On the otherhand, running them in \"yolo\" mode is wildly risky.\n    23→\n    24→To allow our agents to run in a balance of safety and speed, we must disrupt the Lethal Trifecta.\n    25→\n    26→Firstly, we remove their access to the full filesystem - the docker containers have access only to their\n    27→own filespace - only copies are used - no file mounts. Environment variables are only those provided by the host\n    28→to the container. \n    29→\n    30→Second, network access is limited to allowlists to ensure your agents can have e.g. free access to library documentation or your\n    31→internal documentation, but not the internet at large!\n    32→\n    33→\n    34→## Workflows\n    35→\n    36→see our [Workflows](docs/workflows.md) documentation!\n    37→\n    38→## Validated code\n    39→\n    40→Your agents are fast, but that speed shouldn't come at the cost of quality.\n    41→\n    42→Keep your validation checks in the loop with your coding agent - go beyond unit tests!\n    43→- validate complexity measurements\n    44→- automated code review\n    45→- auto-split large commits into stacked branches, individually reviewed and validated to keep commits simple and clean\n    46→- custom script and agent support to add your own checks to the mix\n    47→- failures are tracked and classified for use in autogenerating future validation checks\n    48→- validation failure feedback triggers retries to automatically resolve issues before they reach CI\n    49→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01J6r4TFSa4erK367qsRCDGD","session_id":"6146b7bf-a511-4374-8899-2af97fce0332","uuid":"e5d3c80e-4712-41a8-b74d-332238791832"}
