{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J6r4TFSa4erK367qsRCDGD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my comprehensive exploration report.\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Codebase Exploration\n\nI have thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase. Here's a detailed overview of the project structure, architecture, and conventions:\n\n### Overall Project Structure\n\n**Three Binary Deliverables:**\n1. **`cloche`** - CLI client (cmd/cloche/) - short-lived, talks to daemon via gRPC\n2. **`cloched`** - Daemon (cmd/cloched/) - long-running, manages containers and orchestration\n3. **`cloche-agent`** - In-container agent (cmd/cloche-agent/) - autonomous workflow executor\n\n**Core Directory Layout:**\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/                  # CLI subcommands: run, status, logs, stop, delete, poll, loop, shutdown\n  cloched/                 # Daemon entry point\n  cloche-agent/            # Container agent entry point\n\ninternal/\n  domain/                  # Core types: Run, Workflow, Step, StepExecution, RunState\n  ports/                   # Interfaces: RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, ContainerRuntime, AgentAdapter\n  adapters/                # Implementations:\n    docker/                # Docker container runtime\n    sqlite/                # SQLite persistence\n    grpc/                  # gRPC server\n    web/                   # HTTP web dashboard\n    agents/                # Agent adapters\n      prompt/              # Claude Code prompt adapter\n      generic/             # Generic script executor adapter\n    local/                 # Local subprocess runtime (dev)\n  host/                    # Host workflow orchestration: Executor, Runner, Loop, Task\n  engine/                  # Workflow execution engine\n  dsl/                     # Workflow DSL parser\n  config/                  # TOML configuration\n  protocol/                # Status message protocol, result extraction\n  logstream/               # Unified logging\n  agent/                   # In-container agent runner\n  evolution/               # Self-evolution system (validation feedback)\n```\n\n### Domain Types (Core Concepts)\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - `Run`, `StepExecution`, `RunState`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - `Workflow`, `Step`, `Wire`, `Wiring`, `OutputPath`, `OutputMapping`\n\n**Run States:** `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n\n**Step Types:** `agent`, `script`, `workflow` (host-only)\n\n**Workflow Locations:** `container` or `host`\n\n**Key Structures:**\n- `Run` - tracks workflow execution: ID, state, active steps, timing, container info\n- `Step` - unit of work with name, type, results, config map\n- `Wire` - connects step:result pairs to next step with optional output mappings\n- `StepExecution` - records step start/completion, logs, git refs\n- `OutputPath` - navigates JSON paths for env var injection\n\n### CLI Architecture (cmd/cloche/)\n\n**Subcommands and Their Implementation:**\n1. **`cloche init`** - scaffolds new project (init.go)\n2. **`cloche run`** - launches workflow (main.go:cmdRun())\n3. **`cloche status`** - checks run status (main.go:cmdStatus())\n4. **`cloche logs`** - streams logs, supports --follow via SSE (main.go:cmdLogs(), cmdLogsFollow())\n5. **`cloche poll`** - blocks until run finishes (poll.go)\n6. **`cloche list`** - lists recent runs (main.go:cmdList())\n7. **`cloche stop`** - stops a run (main.go:cmdStop())\n8. **`cloche delete`** - deletes retained container (main.go:cmdDelete())\n9. **`cloche loop`** - starts/stops orchestration loop (main.go:cmdLoop())\n10. **`cloche health`** - project health summary (health.go)\n11. **`cloche shutdown`** - stops daemon (main.go:cmdShutdown())\n\n**Communication:** All commands (except `init`, `health`) connect to daemon via gRPC at `CLOCHE_ADDR` (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n\n### Daemon Implementation (cmd/cloched/main.go)\n\n**Initialization Flow:**\n1. Load global config from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n2. Init SQLite store at `CLOCHE_DB`\n3. Sweep stale runs from crashes\n4. Init container runtime (Docker or local subprocess)\n5. Create gRPC server with ClocheService\n6. Optionally start HTTP web handler at `CLOCHE_HTTP`\n7. Set up evolution trigger if enabled\n8. Auto-run host workflows for active projects\n9. Listen for SIGTERM/SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n\n**Key Services:**\n- `ContainerRuntime` - manages docker containers\n- `RunStore` - persists run state\n- `CaptureStore` - saves step captures\n- `LogStore` - indexes extracted logs\n- `EvolutionTrigger` - optional self-evolution system\n\n### gRPC Service Definition\n\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n**Main RPCs:**\n- `RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) -> RunWorkflowResponse` - launch workflow\n- `GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) -> GetStatusResponse` - check run state\n- `StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) -> stream LogEntry` - stream logs\n- `StopRun(StopRunRequest) -> StopRunResponse` - kill a run\n- `ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) -> ListRunsResponse` - list runs\n- `DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) -> DeleteContainerResponse` - remove container\n- `EnableLoop(EnableLoopRequest) -> EnableLoopResponse` - start orchestration\n- `DisableLoop(DisableLoopRequest) -> DisableLoopResponse` - stop orchestration\n- `Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) -> ShutdownResponse` - stop daemon\n\n### Ports and Adapters (Hexagonal Architecture)\n\n**Interfaces Defined in `/workspace/internal/ports/`:**\n\n1. **RunStore** - persistent run storage\n   - `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, `DeleteRun()`\n   - `ListRuns()`, `ListRunsByProject()`, `ListProjects()`, `ListChildRuns()`\n\n2. **CaptureStore** - step execution capture\n   - `SaveCapture()`, `GetCaptures()`\n\n3. **LogStore** - extracted log file indexing\n   - `SaveLogFile()`, `GetLogFiles()`, `GetLogFilesByStep()`, `GetLogFileByType()`\n\n4. **ContainerRuntime** - container lifecycle\n   - `Start()`, `Stop()`, `AttachOutput()`, `Wait()`, `CopyFrom()`, `Logs()`, `Remove()`, `Inspect()`\n   - Optional: `EnsureImage()` for auto-rebuild\n\n5. **AgentAdapter** - agent execution\n   - `Execute(ctx, step, workDir) -> (result, error)`\n\n6. **EvolutionStore** - self-evolution tracking\n   - `SaveEvolution()`, `GetLastEvolution()`, `ListRunsSince()`\n\n**Adapter Implementations:**\n\n- **SQLite** (`internal/adapters/sqlite/`) - Run, Step, Log, Evolution persistence\n- **Docker** (`internal/adapters/docker/`) - Docker container management\n- **gRPC** (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`) - ClocheServer implements gRPC\n- **Web** (`internal/adapters/web/`) - HTTP dashboard with HTML templates\n- **Prompt** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`) - Claude Code agent invocation\n- **Generic** (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/`) - Shell script executor\n- **Local** (`internal/adapters/local/`) - Subprocess runtime for dev/testing\n\n### Workflow DSL and Parser\n\n**Files:** `internal/dsl/` (lexer.go, parser.go, token.go)\n\n**Features:**\n- Parse container workflows and host workflows\n- Support multiple workflows in host.cloche\n- Lexer/Parser with line/col tracking\n- Validates: all results wired, no orphaned steps, entry point exists\n- Supports wiring, collects, output mappings\n- Config key validation with warnings for typos\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `Parse()` - parse single workflow with location option\n- `ParseForContainer()` - container workflow\n- `ParseForHost()` - single host workflow\n- `ParseAllForHost()` - multiple host workflows\n- `Workflow.Validate()` - validate wiring and structure\n- `Workflow.ValidateLocation()` - ensure workflow_name only in host\n- `Workflow.ValidateConfig()` - warn on unknown keys\n\n### Engine and Execution\n\n**File:** `internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n**Core Execution Model:**\n- `StepExecutor` interface - executes steps, returns result name\n- `StatusHandler` interface - receives step/run events\n- Parallel step execution with channels\n- Result-driven wiring graph traversal\n- Collect clauses for synchronization (all/any)\n- Default 30-minute step timeout, configurable per-step\n- Max 1000 steps per run\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `New(executor StepExecutor)` - create engine\n- `Run(ctx, workflow)` - execute workflow graph\n- `SetStatusHandler()` - attach event listener\n- `SetMaxSteps()`, `SetDefaultTimeout()` - configure\n\n### Host Workflow Orchestration\n\n**Files:** `internal/host/executor.go`, `internal/host/runner.go`, `internal/host/loop.go`, `internal/host/task.go`\n\n**Executor** - runs host workflow steps:\n- Script steps via `sh -c` with env vars\n- Workflow steps via gRPC dispatch + polling\n- Agent steps via prompt adapter\n- Output mappings for env injection\n- Main git worktree detection for script execution\n\n**Runner** - orchestrates three-phase workflow:\n- Parse host.cloche (single or multiple workflows)\n- Create run record in store\n- Execute engine.Run() with executor\n- Persist step events to store\n\n**Loop** - continuous task orchestration:\n- Three-phase: list-tasks → main → finalize\n- Task deduplication within timeout window\n- Concurrent limit (default 1)\n- Stagger delay between launches\n- New phase-based `NewPhaseLoop()` constructor\n- Legacy single-function `NewLoop()` mode\n\n**Task** - work item representation:\n- JSON fields: id, status, title, description, metadata\n- `TaskAssigner` interface for daemon-managed tasks\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner` - runs shell command, parses JSON array\n- `ParseTasksJSONL()` - parses JSONL output\n\n**Environment Variables in Host Steps:**\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - project path\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - where to write output\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - previous step's output\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - task ID for main/finalize\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - main phase result\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - main phase run ID\n- Wire-mapped variables\n\n### Agent Adapters\n\n**Prompt Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`):\n- Invokes Claude Code (or fallback commands)\n- Command fallback chain support\n- Default args for known agents (claude, gemini)\n- Attempt counting for `max_attempts` config\n- Fallback on non-zero exit without result marker\n- Full prompt assembly from template + user + feedback\n\n**Generic Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/`):\n- Executes shell commands\n- Optional status writer for live streaming\n- Result extraction from CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n- Log file writing to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n\n**In-Container Agent Runner** (`internal/agent/runner.go`):\n- Reads workflow from `.cloche/<name>.cloche`\n- Creates both generic and prompt adapters\n- Unified log writer (full.log)\n- Status writer for JSON-line protocol\n- Extracts title from prompt\n- Handles history logging\n\n### Protocol and Communication\n\n**Status Protocol** (`internal/protocol/status.go`):\n- JSON-line format: `{\"type\": \"...\", \"step_name\": \"...\", \"result\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\"}`\n- Message types: step_started, step_completed, run_completed, run_title, log, error\n- StatusWriter with optional flushing\n\n**Result Extraction** (`internal/protocol/result.go`):\n- Marker prefix: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>`\n- Last marker wins\n- Strips markers from output\n- Fallback: exit 0 = success, exit non-zero = fail\n\n**History Logging** (`internal/protocol/history.go`):\n- Appends to `.cloche/history.log`\n- Format: timestamp, step name, result, output (indented)\n- Workflow markers: workflow:start, workflow:end\n\n### Unified Logging\n\n**File:** `internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n\n- Writer to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n- Thread-safe with mutex\n- Types: status, script, llm\n- Format: `[RFC3339] [TYPE] MESSAGE`\n- Log parsing (ParseClaudeStream)\n- Broadcaster for SSE streaming\n\n### Configuration\n\n**File:** `internal/config/config.go`\n\n**Per-Project Config** (`.cloche/config.toml`):\n- `[daemon]` - listen, http, image, db, runtime, agent_path, llm_command\n- `[evolution]` - enabled, debounce_seconds, min_confidence, max_prompt_bullets\n- `[orchestration]` - concurrency, stagger_seconds, list_tasks_command, dedup_seconds\n- `active` - auto-run on daemon start\n\n**Global Config** (`~/.config/cloche/config`):\n- Same structure as per-project\n- Loaded as defaults, overridden by project config\n\n### SQLite Persistence\n\n**File:** `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n**Tables:**\n- `runs` - ID, workflow_name, state, active_steps, timestamps, project_dir, error, container_id, base_sha, etc.\n- `step_executions` - run_id, step_name, result, timestamps, logs, git_ref\n- `log_files` - run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, size, created_at\n- `merge_queue` - run_id, branch, project, status, timestamps\n- `evolution_log` - id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id, classification, changes, knowledge\n\n**Configuration:**\n- WAL mode for concurrent read/write\n- 5-second busy timeout\n- Single connection (serialized access)\n- Max 1 open connection (thread-safe via serialization)\n\n### Docker Container Runtime\n\n**File:** `internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`\n\n**Container Creation:**\n- `docker create` with image, workdir, env vars\n- Default CMD: `cloche-agent .cloche/<workflow>.cloche`\n- Workspace copied via `docker cp` (not mounted)\n- Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` applied on top\n- User wrapping: run as root, chown workspace, exec as agent user\n- ANTHROPIC_API_KEY passed through if set\n- Extra mounts/env via CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS / CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV\n\n**Network:** Full network access (needed for git push, APIs)\n\n**Extraction:** Results extracted via `docker cp` into git worktree\n\n### Web Dashboard\n\n**File:** `internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**Features:**\n- HTTP server (listen on CLOCHE_HTTP)\n- HTML templates with embedded CSS/JS\n- API endpoints (JSON responses)\n- SSE streaming for live logs\n- Project overview, run lists, run details\n- Step output viewing\n- Container management (stop, delete)\n\n**Routes:**\n- `GET /` - project overview\n- `GET /projects/{name}` - project detail\n- `GET /runs` - run list\n- `GET /runs/{id}` - run detail\n- `GET /api/projects` - project list (JSON)\n- `GET /api/runs` - runs (JSON)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` - run detail (JSON)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` - SSE stream\n\n### Self-Evolution System\n\n**Files:** `internal/evolution/` (trigger.go, orchestrator.go, curator.go, classifier.go, etc.)\n\n**Purpose:** Automatically improve workflows based on validation failures\n\n**Components:**\n- `Trigger` - debounce + fire evolution orchestration\n- `Orchestrator` - run classifier, curator, generate script\n- `Classifier` - categorize failures (syntax, runtime, test, validation)\n- `Curator` - select relevant historical context\n- `LLMClient` - invoke LLM for fixes\n\n### Naming and ID Generation\n\n**File:** `internal/domain/namegen.go`\n\n- `GenerateRunID(workflowName)` - uses adjective-noun-UUID format (e.g., \"develop-quiet-jade-abc123\")\n- Human-readable IDs for easy CLI usage\n\n### Key Conventions and Patterns\n\n1. **Hexagonal Architecture** - Core domain independent of infrastructure, interfaces at boundaries\n2. **Context Propagation** - All async operations use context.Context for cancellation\n3. **JSON-line Protocol** - Status messages, task lists, log entries use newline-delimited JSON\n4. **Output Mapping** - Extract JSON paths from step output into env vars for downstream steps\n5. **Result Markers** - CLOCHE_RESULT: prefix for explicit result reporting\n6. **Wiring Separation** - Wires defined separately from steps, enabling self-evolution\n7. **Terminal Steps** - `done` and `abort` as built-in workflow endpoints\n8. **Unified Logging** - All output goes to single full.log with type prefixes\n9. **Retry Loops** - Wire failures back to earlier steps, use max_attempts for caps\n10. **Fanout/Collect** - Support parallel branches with all/any synchronization\n11. **Git Integration** - Results extracted to worktree branches, base SHA captured\n12. **Task-Driven Orchestration** - Three-phase workflow (list → main → finalize) with task dedup\n13. **Config Hierarchy** - Step > Workflow > File > Env var defaults\n14. **Agent Fallback Chains** - Try multiple agents, stop on success or explicit result\n\n### File Paths and Locations\n\n- Workflows: `.cloche/*.cloche`\n- Prompts: `.cloche/prompts/`\n- Scripts: `.cloche/scripts/`\n- Config: `.cloche/config.toml`\n- Dockerfile: `.cloche/Dockerfile`\n- Overrides: `.cloche/overrides/`\n- Runtime: `.cloche/<run-id>/`\n  - `prompt.txt` - user request\n  - `output/` - step logs and full.log\n  - `attempt_count/` - retry counters\n  - `history.log` - step execution log\n- Database: `cloche.db` (SQLite)\n- History: `.cloche/history.log` (host workflows)\n\n### Testing Approach\n\n- Unit tests for components (DSL, engine, storage, adapters)\n- Integration tests with mocks\n- Domain logic tested independently\n- Stretchr testify for assertions\n\n### Build and Deployment\n\n**Makefile Targets:**\n- `make build` - build 3 binaries to bin/\n- `make test` - run all tests\n- `make lint` - go vet\n- `make proto` - regenerate gRPC code\n- `make docker-base` - build cloche-base image\n- `make docker-build` - build cloche-agent image\n- `make install` - build, docker-build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- Go 1.25.3\n- gRPC, protobuf\n- SQLite (modernc.org/sqlite)\n- TOML parser\n- Docker\n\nThis comprehensive overview should provide you with the knowledge needed to add new functionality, modify existing features, or extend the system while maintaining consistency with established patterns and conventions."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aad8258519aee5f4c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 89235\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 82080</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6146b7bf-a511-4374-8899-2af97fce0332","uuid":"8bbcc8dc-c71c-4179-830e-c3fdd8373b17","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - what directories exist under cmd/, internal/, etc.\n2. The domain types - look at internal/domain/ for Task, Run, and related types\n3. The CLI commands - look at cmd/cloche/ for how subcommands are structured\n4. The web dashboard - look for any web/HTTP server code, templates, handlers\n5. The daemon - look at cmd/cloched/ and any gRPC service definitions\n6. The ports/adapters - look at internal/ports/ and internal/adapters/\n7. Any existing task-related code (list-tasks, JSONL parsing, task pipeline)\n8. Proto/gRPC definitions\n\nBe very thorough - read key files in their entirety. I need to understand the conventions used so I can add new functionality.","agentId":"aad8258519aee5f4c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my comprehensive exploration report.\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Codebase Exploration\n\nI have thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase. Here's a detailed overview of the project structure, architecture, and conventions:\n\n### Overall Project Structure\n\n**Three Binary Deliverables:**\n1. **`cloche`** - CLI client (cmd/cloche/) - short-lived, talks to daemon via gRPC\n2. **`cloched`** - Daemon (cmd/cloched/) - long-running, manages containers and orchestration\n3. **`cloche-agent`** - In-container agent (cmd/cloche-agent/) - autonomous workflow executor\n\n**Core Directory Layout:**\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/                  # CLI subcommands: run, status, logs, stop, delete, poll, loop, shutdown\n  cloched/                 # Daemon entry point\n  cloche-agent/            # Container agent entry point\n\ninternal/\n  domain/                  # Core types: Run, Workflow, Step, StepExecution, RunState\n  ports/                   # Interfaces: RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore, ContainerRuntime, AgentAdapter\n  adapters/                # Implementations:\n    docker/                # Docker container runtime\n    sqlite/                # SQLite persistence\n    grpc/                  # gRPC server\n    web/                   # HTTP web dashboard\n    agents/                # Agent adapters\n      prompt/              # Claude Code prompt adapter\n      generic/             # Generic script executor adapter\n    local/                 # Local subprocess runtime (dev)\n  host/                    # Host workflow orchestration: Executor, Runner, Loop, Task\n  engine/                  # Workflow execution engine\n  dsl/                     # Workflow DSL parser\n  config/                  # TOML configuration\n  protocol/                # Status message protocol, result extraction\n  logstream/               # Unified logging\n  agent/                   # In-container agent runner\n  evolution/               # Self-evolution system (validation feedback)\n```\n\n### Domain Types (Core Concepts)\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - `Run`, `StepExecution`, `RunState`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - `Workflow`, `Step`, `Wire`, `Wiring`, `OutputPath`, `OutputMapping`\n\n**Run States:** `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n\n**Step Types:** `agent`, `script`, `workflow` (host-only)\n\n**Workflow Locations:** `container` or `host`\n\n**Key Structures:**\n- `Run` - tracks workflow execution: ID, state, active steps, timing, container info\n- `Step` - unit of work with name, type, results, config map\n- `Wire` - connects step:result pairs to next step with optional output mappings\n- `StepExecution` - records step start/completion, logs, git refs\n- `OutputPath` - navigates JSON paths for env var injection\n\n### CLI Architecture (cmd/cloche/)\n\n**Subcommands and Their Implementation:**\n1. **`cloche init`** - scaffolds new project (init.go)\n2. **`cloche run`** - launches workflow (main.go:cmdRun())\n3. **`cloche status`** - checks run status (main.go:cmdStatus())\n4. **`cloche logs`** - streams logs, supports --follow via SSE (main.go:cmdLogs(), cmdLogsFollow())\n5. **`cloche poll`** - blocks until run finishes (poll.go)\n6. **`cloche list`** - lists recent runs (main.go:cmdList())\n7. **`cloche stop`** - stops a run (main.go:cmdStop())\n8. **`cloche delete`** - deletes retained container (main.go:cmdDelete())\n9. **`cloche loop`** - starts/stops orchestration loop (main.go:cmdLoop())\n10. **`cloche health`** - project health summary (health.go)\n11. **`cloche shutdown`** - stops daemon (main.go:cmdShutdown())\n\n**Communication:** All commands (except `init`, `health`) connect to daemon via gRPC at `CLOCHE_ADDR` (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n\n### Daemon Implementation (cmd/cloched/main.go)\n\n**Initialization Flow:**\n1. Load global config from `~/.config/cloche/config`\n2. Init SQLite store at `CLOCHE_DB`\n3. Sweep stale runs from crashes\n4. Init container runtime (Docker or local subprocess)\n5. Create gRPC server with ClocheService\n6. Optionally start HTTP web handler at `CLOCHE_HTTP`\n7. Set up evolution trigger if enabled\n8. Auto-run host workflows for active projects\n9. Listen for SIGTERM/SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n\n**Key Services:**\n- `ContainerRuntime` - manages docker containers\n- `RunStore` - persists run state\n- `CaptureStore` - saves step captures\n- `LogStore` - indexes extracted logs\n- `EvolutionTrigger` - optional self-evolution system\n\n### gRPC Service Definition\n\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n**Main RPCs:**\n- `RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) -> RunWorkflowResponse` - launch workflow\n- `GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) -> GetStatusResponse` - check run state\n- `StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) -> stream LogEntry` - stream logs\n- `StopRun(StopRunRequest) -> StopRunResponse` - kill a run\n- `ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) -> ListRunsResponse` - list runs\n- `DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) -> DeleteContainerResponse` - remove container\n- `EnableLoop(EnableLoopRequest) -> EnableLoopResponse` - start orchestration\n- `DisableLoop(DisableLoopRequest) -> DisableLoopResponse` - stop orchestration\n- `Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) -> ShutdownResponse` - stop daemon\n\n### Ports and Adapters (Hexagonal Architecture)\n\n**Interfaces Defined in `/workspace/internal/ports/`:**\n\n1. **RunStore** - persistent run storage\n   - `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, `DeleteRun()`\n   - `ListRuns()`, `ListRunsByProject()`, `ListProjects()`, `ListChildRuns()`\n\n2. **CaptureStore** - step execution capture\n   - `SaveCapture()`, `GetCaptures()`\n\n3. **LogStore** - extracted log file indexing\n   - `SaveLogFile()`, `GetLogFiles()`, `GetLogFilesByStep()`, `GetLogFileByType()`\n\n4. **ContainerRuntime** - container lifecycle\n   - `Start()`, `Stop()`, `AttachOutput()`, `Wait()`, `CopyFrom()`, `Logs()`, `Remove()`, `Inspect()`\n   - Optional: `EnsureImage()` for auto-rebuild\n\n5. **AgentAdapter** - agent execution\n   - `Execute(ctx, step, workDir) -> (result, error)`\n\n6. **EvolutionStore** - self-evolution tracking\n   - `SaveEvolution()`, `GetLastEvolution()`, `ListRunsSince()`\n\n**Adapter Implementations:**\n\n- **SQLite** (`internal/adapters/sqlite/`) - Run, Step, Log, Evolution persistence\n- **Docker** (`internal/adapters/docker/`) - Docker container management\n- **gRPC** (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`) - ClocheServer implements gRPC\n- **Web** (`internal/adapters/web/`) - HTTP dashboard with HTML templates\n- **Prompt** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`) - Claude Code agent invocation\n- **Generic** (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/`) - Shell script executor\n- **Local** (`internal/adapters/local/`) - Subprocess runtime for dev/testing\n\n### Workflow DSL and Parser\n\n**Files:** `internal/dsl/` (lexer.go, parser.go, token.go)\n\n**Features:**\n- Parse container workflows and host workflows\n- Support multiple workflows in host.cloche\n- Lexer/Parser with line/col tracking\n- Validates: all results wired, no orphaned steps, entry point exists\n- Supports wiring, collects, output mappings\n- Config key validation with warnings for typos\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `Parse()` - parse single workflow with location option\n- `ParseForContainer()` - container workflow\n- `ParseForHost()` - single host workflow\n- `ParseAllForHost()` - multiple host workflows\n- `Workflow.Validate()` - validate wiring and structure\n- `Workflow.ValidateLocation()` - ensure workflow_name only in host\n- `Workflow.ValidateConfig()` - warn on unknown keys\n\n### Engine and Execution\n\n**File:** `internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n**Core Execution Model:**\n- `StepExecutor` interface - executes steps, returns result name\n- `StatusHandler` interface - receives step/run events\n- Parallel step execution with channels\n- Result-driven wiring graph traversal\n- Collect clauses for synchronization (all/any)\n- Default 30-minute step timeout, configurable per-step\n- Max 1000 steps per run\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `New(executor StepExecutor)` - create engine\n- `Run(ctx, workflow)` - execute workflow graph\n- `SetStatusHandler()` - attach event listener\n- `SetMaxSteps()`, `SetDefaultTimeout()` - configure\n\n### Host Workflow Orchestration\n\n**Files:** `internal/host/executor.go`, `internal/host/runner.go`, `internal/host/loop.go`, `internal/host/task.go`\n\n**Executor** - runs host workflow steps:\n- Script steps via `sh -c` with env vars\n- Workflow steps via gRPC dispatch + polling\n- Agent steps via prompt adapter\n- Output mappings for env injection\n- Main git worktree detection for script execution\n\n**Runner** - orchestrates three-phase workflow:\n- Parse host.cloche (single or multiple workflows)\n- Create run record in store\n- Execute engine.Run() with executor\n- Persist step events to store\n\n**Loop** - continuous task orchestration:\n- Three-phase: list-tasks → main → finalize\n- Task deduplication within timeout window\n- Concurrent limit (default 1)\n- Stagger delay between launches\n- New phase-based `NewPhaseLoop()` constructor\n- Legacy single-function `NewLoop()` mode\n\n**Task** - work item representation:\n- JSON fields: id, status, title, description, metadata\n- `TaskAssigner` interface for daemon-managed tasks\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner` - runs shell command, parses JSON array\n- `ParseTasksJSONL()` - parses JSONL output\n\n**Environment Variables in Host Steps:**\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - project path\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - where to write output\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - previous step's output\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - task ID for main/finalize\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - main phase result\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - main phase run ID\n- Wire-mapped variables\n\n### Agent Adapters\n\n**Prompt Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`):\n- Invokes Claude Code (or fallback commands)\n- Command fallback chain support\n- Default args for known agents (claude, gemini)\n- Attempt counting for `max_attempts` config\n- Fallback on non-zero exit without result marker\n- Full prompt assembly from template + user + feedback\n\n**Generic Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/`):\n- Executes shell commands\n- Optional status writer for live streaming\n- Result extraction from CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n- Log file writing to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n\n**In-Container Agent Runner** (`internal/agent/runner.go`):\n- Reads workflow from `.cloche/<name>.cloche`\n- Creates both generic and prompt adapters\n- Unified log writer (full.log)\n- Status writer for JSON-line protocol\n- Extracts title from prompt\n- Handles history logging\n\n### Protocol and Communication\n\n**Status Protocol** (`internal/protocol/status.go`):\n- JSON-line format: `{\"type\": \"...\", \"step_name\": \"...\", \"result\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\"}`\n- Message types: step_started, step_completed, run_completed, run_title, log, error\n- StatusWriter with optional flushing\n\n**Result Extraction** (`internal/protocol/result.go`):\n- Marker prefix: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>`\n- Last marker wins\n- Strips markers from output\n- Fallback: exit 0 = success, exit non-zero = fail\n\n**History Logging** (`internal/protocol/history.go`):\n- Appends to `.cloche/history.log`\n- Format: timestamp, step name, result, output (indented)\n- Workflow markers: workflow:start, workflow:end\n\n### Unified Logging\n\n**File:** `internal/logstream/logstream.go`\n\n- Writer to `.cloche/output/full.log`\n- Thread-safe with mutex\n- Types: status, script, llm\n- Format: `[RFC3339] [TYPE] MESSAGE`\n- Log parsing (ParseClaudeStream)\n- Broadcaster for SSE streaming\n\n### Configuration\n\n**File:** `internal/config/config.go`\n\n**Per-Project Config** (`.cloche/config.toml`):\n- `[daemon]` - listen, http, image, db, runtime, agent_path, llm_command\n- `[evolution]` - enabled, debounce_seconds, min_confidence, max_prompt_bullets\n- `[orchestration]` - concurrency, stagger_seconds, list_tasks_command, dedup_seconds\n- `active` - auto-run on daemon start\n\n**Global Config** (`~/.config/cloche/config`):\n- Same structure as per-project\n- Loaded as defaults, overridden by project config\n\n### SQLite Persistence\n\n**File:** `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n**Tables:**\n- `runs` - ID, workflow_name, state, active_steps, timestamps, project_dir, error, container_id, base_sha, etc.\n- `step_executions` - run_id, step_name, result, timestamps, logs, git_ref\n- `log_files` - run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, size, created_at\n- `merge_queue` - run_id, branch, project, status, timestamps\n- `evolution_log` - id, project_dir, workflow_name, trigger_run_id, classification, changes, knowledge\n\n**Configuration:**\n- WAL mode for concurrent read/write\n- 5-second busy timeout\n- Single connection (serialized access)\n- Max 1 open connection (thread-safe via serialization)\n\n### Docker Container Runtime\n\n**File:** `internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`\n\n**Container Creation:**\n- `docker create` with image, workdir, env vars\n- Default CMD: `cloche-agent .cloche/<workflow>.cloche`\n- Workspace copied via `docker cp` (not mounted)\n- Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` applied on top\n- User wrapping: run as root, chown workspace, exec as agent user\n- ANTHROPIC_API_KEY passed through if set\n- Extra mounts/env via CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS / CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV\n\n**Network:** Full network access (needed for git push, APIs)\n\n**Extraction:** Results extracted via `docker cp` into git worktree\n\n### Web Dashboard\n\n**File:** `internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**Features:**\n- HTTP server (listen on CLOCHE_HTTP)\n- HTML templates with embedded CSS/JS\n- API endpoints (JSON responses)\n- SSE streaming for live logs\n- Project overview, run lists, run details\n- Step output viewing\n- Container management (stop, delete)\n\n**Routes:**\n- `GET /` - project overview\n- `GET /projects/{name}` - project detail\n- `GET /runs` - run list\n- `GET /runs/{id}` - run detail\n- `GET /api/projects` - project list (JSON)\n- `GET /api/runs` - runs (JSON)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` - run detail (JSON)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` - SSE stream\n\n### Self-Evolution System\n\n**Files:** `internal/evolution/` (trigger.go, orchestrator.go, curator.go, classifier.go, etc.)\n\n**Purpose:** Automatically improve workflows based on validation failures\n\n**Components:**\n- `Trigger` - debounce + fire evolution orchestration\n- `Orchestrator` - run classifier, curator, generate script\n- `Classifier` - categorize failures (syntax, runtime, test, validation)\n- `Curator` - select relevant historical context\n- `LLMClient` - invoke LLM for fixes\n\n### Naming and ID Generation\n\n**File:** `internal/domain/namegen.go`\n\n- `GenerateRunID(workflowName)` - uses adjective-noun-UUID format (e.g., \"develop-quiet-jade-abc123\")\n- Human-readable IDs for easy CLI usage\n\n### Key Conventions and Patterns\n\n1. **Hexagonal Architecture** - Core domain independent of infrastructure, interfaces at boundaries\n2. **Context Propagation** - All async operations use context.Context for cancellation\n3. **JSON-line Protocol** - Status messages, task lists, log entries use newline-delimited JSON\n4. **Output Mapping** - Extract JSON paths from step output into env vars for downstream steps\n5. **Result Markers** - CLOCHE_RESULT: prefix for explicit result reporting\n6. **Wiring Separation** - Wires defined separately from steps, enabling self-evolution\n7. **Terminal Steps** - `done` and `abort` as built-in workflow endpoints\n8. **Unified Logging** - All output goes to single full.log with type prefixes\n9. **Retry Loops** - Wire failures back to earlier steps, use max_attempts for caps\n10. **Fanout/Collect** - Support parallel branches with all/any synchronization\n11. **Git Integration** - Results extracted to worktree branches, base SHA captured\n12. **Task-Driven Orchestration** - Three-phase workflow (list → main → finalize) with task dedup\n13. **Config Hierarchy** - Step > Workflow > File > Env var defaults\n14. **Agent Fallback Chains** - Try multiple agents, stop on success or explicit result\n\n### File Paths and Locations\n\n- Workflows: `.cloche/*.cloche`\n- Prompts: `.cloche/prompts/`\n- Scripts: `.cloche/scripts/`\n- Config: `.cloche/config.toml`\n- Dockerfile: `.cloche/Dockerfile`\n- Overrides: `.cloche/overrides/`\n- Runtime: `.cloche/<run-id>/`\n  - `prompt.txt` - user request\n  - `output/` - step logs and full.log\n  - `attempt_count/` - retry counters\n  - `history.log` - step execution log\n- Database: `cloche.db` (SQLite)\n- History: `.cloche/history.log` (host workflows)\n\n### Testing Approach\n\n- Unit tests for components (DSL, engine, storage, adapters)\n- Integration tests with mocks\n- Domain logic tested independently\n- Stretchr testify for assertions\n\n### Build and Deployment\n\n**Makefile Targets:**\n- `make build` - build 3 binaries to bin/\n- `make test` - run all tests\n- `make lint` - go vet\n- `make proto` - regenerate gRPC code\n- `make docker-base` - build cloche-base image\n- `make docker-build` - build cloche-agent image\n- `make install` - build, docker-build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- Go 1.25.3\n- gRPC, protobuf\n- SQLite (modernc.org/sqlite)\n- TOML parser\n- Docker\n\nThis comprehensive overview should provide you with the knowledge needed to add new functionality, modify existing features, or extend the system while maintaining consistency with established patterns and conventions."}],"totalDurationMs":82080,"totalTokens":89235,"totalToolUseCount":44,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2024,"cache_read_input_tokens":82261,"output_tokens":4943,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2024},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
