{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pit2SXhkGbCbkNiWPACjB6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package main\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bufio\"\n     5→\t\"context\"\n     6→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     7→\t\"errors\"\n     8→\t\"fmt\"\n     9→\t\"io\"\n    10→\t\"net/http\"\n    11→\t\"os\"\n    12→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    13→\t\"strings\"\n    14→\t\"time\"\n    15→\n    16→\tpb \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb\"\n    17→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n    18→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n    19→\t\"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n    20→\t\"google.golang.org/grpc/credentials/insecure\"\n    21→)\n    22→\n    23→func main() {\n    24→\tif len(os.Args) < 2 {\n    25→\t\tusage()\n    26→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n    27→\t}\n    28→\n    29→\t// Commands that don't need a daemon connection\n    30→\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n    31→\tcase \"init\":\n    32→\t\tcmdInit(os.Args[2:])\n    33→\t\treturn\n    34→\tcase \"health\":\n    35→\t\tcmdHealth(os.Args[2:])\n    36→\t\treturn\n    37→\t}\n    38→\n    39→\t// Commands that need a daemon connection\n    40→\taddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_ADDR\")\n    41→\tif addr == \"\" {\n    42→\t\taddr = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\n    43→\t}\n    44→\n    45→\tconn, err := grpc.NewClient(addr, grpc.WithTransportCredentials(insecure.NewCredentials()))\n    46→\tif err != nil {\n    47→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"failed to connect: %v\\n\", err)\n    48→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n    49→\t}\n    50→\tdefer conn.Close()\n    51→\n    52→\tclient := pb.NewClocheServiceClient(conn)\n    53→\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n    54→\tdefer cancel()\n    55→\n    56→\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n    57→\tcase \"run\":\n    58→\t\tcmdRun(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n    59→\tcase \"status\":\n    60→\t\tcmdStatus(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n    61→\tcase \"logs\":\n    62→\t\tcmdLogs(client, os.Args[2:])\n    63→\tcase \"poll\":\n    64→\t\tcmdPoll(client, os.Args[2:])\n    65→\tcase \"list\":\n    66→\t\tcmdList(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n    67→\tcase \"stop\":\n    68→\t\tcmdStop(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n    69→\tcase \"delete\":\n    70→\t\tcmdDelete(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n    71→\tcase \"loop\":\n    72→\t\tcmdLoop(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n    73→\tcase \"shutdown\":\n    74→\t\tcmdShutdown(ctx, client)\n    75→\tdefault:\n    76→\t\tusage()\n    77→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n    78→\t}\n    79→}\n    80→\n    81→func usage() {\n    82→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, `usage: cloche <command> [args]\n    83→\n    84→Commands:\n    85→  init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n    86→                                             Initialize a Cloche project\n    87→  health                                   Show project health summary\n    88→  run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n    89→                                             Launch a workflow run\n    90→  status <run-id>                            Check run status\n    91→  logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n    92→                                             Show logs for a run\n    93→  poll <run-id>                              Wait for a run to finish\n    94→  list [--all]                                List runs (last hour by default)\n    95→  stop <run-id>                              Stop a running workflow\n    96→  delete <container-or-run-id>               Delete a retained container\n    97→  loop [--max <n>]                            Start orchestration loop (default max=1)\n    98→  loop stop                                  Stop orchestration loop\n    99→  shutdown                                   Shut down the daemon\n   100→`)\n   101→}\n   102→\n   103→func cmdRun(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   104→\tvar workflow, prompt, title string\n   105→\tvar keepContainer bool\n   106→\n   107→\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n   108→\t\tswitch args[i] {\n   109→\t\tcase \"--workflow\":\n   110→\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   111→\t\t\t\ti++\n   112→\t\t\t\tworkflow = args[i]\n   113→\t\t\t}\n   114→\t\tcase \"--prompt\", \"-p\":\n   115→\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   116→\t\t\t\ti++\n   117→\t\t\t\tprompt = args[i]\n   118→\t\t\t}\n   119→\t\tcase \"--title\":\n   120→\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   121→\t\t\t\ti++\n   122→\t\t\t\ttitle = args[i]\n   123→\t\t\t}\n   124→\t\tcase \"--keep-container\":\n   125→\t\t\tkeepContainer = true\n   126→\t\tdefault:\n   127→\t\t\t// Support bare positional arg as workflow name for backwards compat\n   128→\t\t\tif workflow == \"\" && !strings.HasPrefix(args[i], \"-\") {\n   129→\t\t\t\tworkflow = args[i]\n   130→\t\t\t}\n   131→\t\t}\n   132→\t}\n   133→\n   134→\tif workflow == \"\" {\n   135→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \\\"...\\\"] [--title \\\"...\\\"]\\n\")\n   136→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   137→\t}\n   138→\n   139→\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n   140→\n   141→\t// Resolve image from workflow file (soft failure — fall back to daemon default)\n   142→\tvar image string\n   143→\twfPath := filepath.Join(cwd, \".cloche\", workflow+\".cloche\")\n   144→\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(wfPath); err == nil {\n   145→\t\tif wf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data)); err == nil {\n   146→\t\t\timage = wf.Config[\"container.image\"]\n   147→\t\t}\n   148→\t}\n   149→\n   150→\tresp, err := client.RunWorkflow(ctx, &pb.RunWorkflowRequest{\n   151→\t\tWorkflowName:  workflow,\n   152→\t\tProjectDir:    cwd,\n   153→\t\tImage:         image,\n   154→\t\tPrompt:        prompt,\n   155→\t\tKeepContainer: keepContainer,\n   156→\t\tTitle:         title,\n   157→\t})\n   158→\tif err != nil {\n   159→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   160→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   161→\t}\n   162→\tfmt.Printf(\"Started run: %s\\n\", resp.RunId)\n   163→}\n   164→\n   165→func cmdStatus(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   166→\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   167→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche status <run-id>\\n\")\n   168→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   169→\t}\n   170→\n   171→\tresp, err := client.GetStatus(ctx, &pb.GetStatusRequest{RunId: args[0]})\n   172→\tif err != nil {\n   173→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   174→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   175→\t}\n   176→\n   177→\tfmt.Printf(\"Run:       %s\\n\", resp.RunId)\n   178→\tif resp.Title != \"\" {\n   179→\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Title:     %s\\n\", resp.Title)\n   180→\t}\n   181→\tfmt.Printf(\"Workflow:  %s\\n\", resp.WorkflowName)\n   182→\tif resp.IsHost {\n   183→\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Type:      host\\n\")\n   184→\t} else {\n   185→\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Type:      container\\n\")\n   186→\t}\n   187→\tfmt.Printf(\"State:     %s\\n\", resp.State)\n   188→\tif resp.ContainerId != \"\" {\n   189→\t\tcid := resp.ContainerId\n   190→\t\tif len(cid) > 12 {\n   191→\t\t\tcid = cid[:12]\n   192→\t\t}\n   193→\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Container: %s\\n\", cid)\n   194→\t}\n   195→\tif resp.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n   196→\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Error:     %s\\n\", resp.ErrorMessage)\n   197→\t}\n   198→\tfmt.Printf(\"Active:    %s\\n\", resp.CurrentStep)\n   199→\tfor _, exec := range resp.StepExecutions {\n   200→\t\tfmt.Printf(\"  %s: %s (%s -> %s)\\n\", exec.StepName, exec.Result, exec.StartedAt, exec.CompletedAt)\n   201→\t}\n   202→}\n   203→\n   204→func cmdList(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   205→\tvar all bool\n   206→\tfor _, arg := range args {\n   207→\t\tif arg == \"--all\" {\n   208→\t\t\tall = true\n   209→\t\t}\n   210→\t}\n   211→\n   212→\tresp, err := client.ListRuns(ctx, &pb.ListRunsRequest{All: all})\n   213→\tif err != nil {\n   214→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   215→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   216→\t}\n   217→\n   218→\tif len(resp.Runs) == 0 {\n   219→\t\tfmt.Println(\"No runs found.\")\n   220→\t\treturn\n   221→\t}\n   222→\n   223→\tfor _, run := range resp.Runs {\n   224→\t\trunType := \"container\"\n   225→\t\tif run.IsHost {\n   226→\t\t\trunType = \"host\"\n   227→\t\t}\n   228→\t\tline := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s  %-20s  %-10s  %-9s\", run.RunId, run.WorkflowName, run.State, runType)\n   229→\t\tif run.Title != \"\" {\n   230→\t\t\tt := run.Title\n   231→\t\t\tif len(t) > 40 {\n   232→\t\t\t\tt = t[:37] + \"...\"\n   233→\t\t\t}\n   234→\t\t\tline += \"  \" + t\n   235→\t\t}\n   236→\t\tif run.ContainerId != \"\" {\n   237→\t\t\tline += \"  \" + run.ContainerId\n   238→\t\t}\n   239→\t\tif run.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n   240→\t\t\terrMsg := run.ErrorMessage\n   241→\t\t\tif len(errMsg) > 60 {\n   242→\t\t\t\terrMsg = errMsg[:57] + \"...\"\n   243→\t\t\t}\n   244→\t\t\tline += \"  \" + errMsg\n   245→\t\t}\n   246→\t\tfmt.Println(line)\n   247→\t}\n   248→}\n   249→\n   250→func cmdLogs(client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   251→\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   252→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\\n\")\n   253→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   254→\t}\n   255→\n   256→\tvar stepFilter, typeFilter string\n   257→\tvar follow bool\n   258→\trunID := args[0]\n   259→\n   260→\tfor i := 1; i < len(args); i++ {\n   261→\t\tswitch args[i] {\n   262→\t\tcase \"--step\":\n   263→\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   264→\t\t\t\ti++\n   265→\t\t\t\tstepFilter = args[i]\n   266→\t\t\t}\n   267→\t\tcase \"--type\":\n   268→\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   269→\t\t\t\ti++\n   270→\t\t\t\ttypeFilter = args[i]\n   271→\t\t\t}\n   272→\t\tcase \"--follow\", \"-f\":\n   273→\t\t\tfollow = true\n   274→\t\t}\n   275→\t}\n   276→\n   277→\tif follow {\n   278→\t\tcmdLogsFollow(runID)\n   279→\t\treturn\n   280→\t}\n   281→\n   282→\t// Use background context — log output can be large\n   283→\tstream, err := client.StreamLogs(context.Background(), &pb.StreamLogsRequest{\n   284→\t\tRunId:    runID,\n   285→\t\tStepName: stepFilter,\n   286→\t\tLogType:  typeFilter,\n   287→\t})\n   288→\tif err != nil {\n   289→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   290→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   291→\t}\n   292→\n   293→\tfor {\n   294→\t\tentry, err := stream.Recv()\n   295→\t\tif err != nil {\n   296→\t\t\tif errors.Is(err, io.EOF) {\n   297→\t\t\t\tbreak\n   298→\t\t\t}\n   299→\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error reading logs: %v\\n\", err)\n   300→\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   301→\t\t}\n   302→\n   303→\t\tswitch entry.Type {\n   304→\t\tcase \"step_started\":\n   305→\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s started ---\\n\", entry.StepName)\n   306→\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n   307→\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"%s\\n\", entry.Message)\n   308→\t\t\t}\n   309→\t\tcase \"step_completed\":\n   310→\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s: %s ---\\n\", entry.StepName, entry.Result)\n   311→\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n   312→\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"%s\\n\", entry.Message)\n   313→\t\t\t}\n   314→\t\tcase \"run_completed\":\n   315→\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"\\nRun result: %s\\n\", entry.Result)\n   316→\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n   317→\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Error:      %s\\n\", entry.Message)\n   318→\t\t\t}\n   319→\t\tcase \"full_log\":\n   320→\t\t\tfmt.Print(string(logstream.ParseClaudeStream([]byte(entry.Message))))\n   321→\t\tcase \"log\":\n   322→\t\t\t// Live-streamed log line from an active run.\n   323→\t\t\tfmt.Println(entry.Message)\n   324→\t\tdefault:\n   325→\t\t\t// Handles filtered log entries like \"script_log\", \"llm_log\", \"step_log\"\n   326→\t\t\tif entry.StepName != \"\" {\n   327→\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s ---\\n\", entry.StepName)\n   328→\t\t\t}\n   329→\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n   330→\t\t\t\tfmt.Print(string(logstream.ParseClaudeStream([]byte(entry.Message))))\n   331→\t\t\t}\n   332→\t\t}\n   333→\t}\n   334→}\n   335→\n   336→func cmdLogsFollow(runID string) {\n   337→\t// Determine HTTP address from env\n   338→\thttpAddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_HTTP\")\n   339→\tif httpAddr == \"\" {\n   340→\t\thttpAddr = \"localhost:8080\"\n   341→\t}\n   342→\t// Strip protocol prefix if present\n   343→\thttpAddr = strings.TrimPrefix(httpAddr, \"http://\")\n   344→\n   345→\tsseURL := fmt.Sprintf(\"http://%s/api/runs/%s/stream\", httpAddr, runID)\n   346→\treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"GET\", sseURL, nil)\n   347→\tif err != nil {\n   348→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   349→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   350→\t}\n   351→\treq.Header.Set(\"Accept\", \"text/event-stream\")\n   352→\n   353→\tresp, err := http.DefaultClient.Do(req)\n   354→\tif err != nil {\n   355→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error connecting to SSE stream: %v\\n\", err)\n   356→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   357→\t}\n   358→\tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n   359→\n   360→\tif resp.StatusCode != 200 {\n   361→\t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n   362→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: HTTP %d: %s\\n\", resp.StatusCode, strings.TrimSpace(string(body)))\n   363→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   364→\t}\n   365→\n   366→\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(resp.Body)\n   367→\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n   368→\t\tline := scanner.Text()\n   369→\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(line, \"event: done\") {\n   370→\t\t\tbreak\n   371→\t\t}\n   372→\t\tif !strings.HasPrefix(line, \"data: \") {\n   373→\t\t\tcontinue\n   374→\t\t}\n   375→\t\tdata := strings.TrimPrefix(line, \"data: \")\n   376→\n   377→\t\tvar entry struct {\n   378→\t\t\tTimestamp string `json:\"timestamp\"`\n   379→\t\t\tType      string `json:\"type\"`\n   380→\t\t\tContent   string `json:\"content\"`\n   381→\t\t}\n   382→\t\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &entry); err != nil {\n   383→\t\t\tcontinue\n   384→\t\t}\n   385→\n   386→\t\t// Color-code by type\n   387→\t\tswitch entry.Type {\n   388→\t\tcase \"status\":\n   389→\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"\\033[34m[%s] [%s] %s\\033[0m\\n\", entry.Timestamp, entry.Type, entry.Content)\n   390→\t\tcase \"llm\":\n   391→\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"\\033[32m[%s] [%s] %s\\033[0m\\n\", entry.Timestamp, entry.Type, entry.Content)\n   392→\t\tdefault:\n   393→\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"[%s] [%s] %s\\n\", entry.Timestamp, entry.Type, entry.Content)\n   394→\t\t}\n   395→\t}\n   396→}\n   397→\n   398→func cmdStop(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   399→\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   400→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche stop <run-id>\\n\")\n   401→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   402→\t}\n   403→\n   404→\t_, err := client.StopRun(ctx, &pb.StopRunRequest{RunId: args[0]})\n   405→\tif err != nil {\n   406→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   407→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   408→\t}\n   409→\tfmt.Printf(\"Stopped run: %s\\n\", args[0])\n   410→}\n   411→\n   412→func cmdDelete(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   413→\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   414→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\\n\")\n   415→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   416→\t}\n   417→\n   418→\t_, err := client.DeleteContainer(ctx, &pb.DeleteContainerRequest{Id: args[0]})\n   419→\tif err != nil {\n   420→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   421→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   422→\t}\n   423→\tfmt.Printf(\"Deleted container: %s\\n\", args[0])\n   424→}\n   425→\n   426→func cmdLoop(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   427→\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n   428→\n   429→\t// Check for \"stop\" subcommand\n   430→\tif len(args) > 0 && args[0] == \"stop\" {\n   431→\t\t_, err := client.DisableLoop(ctx, &pb.DisableLoopRequest{ProjectDir: cwd})\n   432→\t\tif err != nil {\n   433→\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   434→\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   435→\t\t}\n   436→\t\tfmt.Println(\"Orchestration loop stopped.\")\n   437→\t\treturn\n   438→\t}\n   439→\n   440→\t// Default: 0 means \"use config value\" (server reads .cloche/config.toml).\n   441→\tvar maxConcurrent int32\n   442→\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n   443→\t\tswitch args[i] {\n   444→\t\tcase \"--max\":\n   445→\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   446→\t\t\t\ti++\n   447→\t\t\t\tn, err := fmt.Sscanf(args[i], \"%d\", &maxConcurrent)\n   448→\t\t\t\tif n != 1 || err != nil {\n   449→\t\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"invalid --max value: %s\\n\", args[i])\n   450→\t\t\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   451→\t\t\t\t}\n   452→\t\t\t}\n   453→\t\t}\n   454→\t}\n   455→\n   456→\t_, err := client.EnableLoop(ctx, &pb.EnableLoopRequest{\n   457→\t\tProjectDir:    cwd,\n   458→\t\tMaxConcurrent: maxConcurrent,\n   459→\t})\n   460→\tif err != nil {\n   461→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   462→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   463→\t}\n   464→\tif maxConcurrent > 0 {\n   465→\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Orchestration loop started (max_concurrent=%d).\\n\", maxConcurrent)\n   466→\t} else {\n   467→\t\tfmt.Println(\"Orchestration loop started (using config defaults).\")\n   468→\t}\n   469→}\n   470→\n   471→func cmdShutdown(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient) {\n   472→\t_, err := client.Shutdown(ctx, &pb.ShutdownRequest{})\n   473→\tif err != nil {\n   474→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   475→\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   476→\t}\n   477→\tfmt.Println(\"Daemon shutting down.\")\n   478→}\n   479→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6146b7bf-a511-4374-8899-2af97fce0332","uuid":"e63641c1-7321-4560-a838-aab15eebd601","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go","content":"package main\n\nimport (\n\t\"bufio\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"io\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tpb \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n\t\"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n\t\"google.golang.org/grpc/credentials/insecure\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n\tif len(os.Args) < 2 {\n\t\tusage()\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\t// Commands that don't need a daemon connection\n\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n\tcase \"init\":\n\t\tcmdInit(os.Args[2:])\n\t\treturn\n\tcase \"health\":\n\t\tcmdHealth(os.Args[2:])\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Commands that need a daemon connection\n\taddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_ADDR\")\n\tif addr == \"\" {\n\t\taddr = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\n\t}\n\n\tconn, err := grpc.NewClient(addr, grpc.WithTransportCredentials(insecure.NewCredentials()))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"failed to connect: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tdefer conn.Close()\n\n\tclient := pb.NewClocheServiceClient(conn)\n\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n\tdefer cancel()\n\n\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n\tcase \"run\":\n\t\tcmdRun(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n\tcase \"status\":\n\t\tcmdStatus(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n\tcase \"logs\":\n\t\tcmdLogs(client, os.Args[2:])\n\tcase \"poll\":\n\t\tcmdPoll(client, os.Args[2:])\n\tcase \"list\":\n\t\tcmdList(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n\tcase \"stop\":\n\t\tcmdStop(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n\tcase \"delete\":\n\t\tcmdDelete(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n\tcase \"loop\":\n\t\tcmdLoop(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n\tcase \"shutdown\":\n\t\tcmdShutdown(ctx, client)\n\tdefault:\n\t\tusage()\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc usage() {\n\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, `usage: cloche <command> [args]\n\nCommands:\n  init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n                                             Initialize a Cloche project\n  health                                   Show project health summary\n  run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n                                             Launch a workflow run\n  status <run-id>                            Check run status\n  logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n                                             Show logs for a run\n  poll <run-id>                              Wait for a run to finish\n  list [--all]                                List runs (last hour by default)\n  stop <run-id>                              Stop a running workflow\n  delete <container-or-run-id>               Delete a retained container\n  loop [--max <n>]                            Start orchestration loop (default max=1)\n  loop stop                                  Stop orchestration loop\n  shutdown                                   Shut down the daemon\n`)\n}\n\nfunc cmdRun(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n\tvar workflow, prompt, title string\n\tvar keepContainer bool\n\n\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n\t\tswitch args[i] {\n\t\tcase \"--workflow\":\n\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n\t\t\t\ti++\n\t\t\t\tworkflow = args[i]\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"--prompt\", \"-p\":\n\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n\t\t\t\ti++\n\t\t\t\tprompt = args[i]\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"--title\":\n\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n\t\t\t\ti++\n\t\t\t\ttitle = args[i]\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"--keep-container\":\n\t\t\tkeepContainer = true\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\t// Support bare positional arg as workflow name for backwards compat\n\t\t\tif workflow == \"\" && !strings.HasPrefix(args[i], \"-\") {\n\t\t\t\tworkflow = args[i]\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tif workflow == \"\" {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \\\"...\\\"] [--title \\\"...\\\"]\\n\")\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n\n\t// Resolve image from workflow file (soft failure — fall back to daemon default)\n\tvar image string\n\twfPath := filepath.Join(cwd, \".cloche\", workflow+\".cloche\")\n\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(wfPath); err == nil {\n\t\tif wf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data)); err == nil {\n\t\t\timage = wf.Config[\"container.image\"]\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tresp, err := client.RunWorkflow(ctx, &pb.RunWorkflowRequest{\n\t\tWorkflowName:  workflow,\n\t\tProjectDir:    cwd,\n\t\tImage:         image,\n\t\tPrompt:        prompt,\n\t\tKeepContainer: keepContainer,\n\t\tTitle:         title,\n\t})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tfmt.Printf(\"Started run: %s\\n\", resp.RunId)\n}\n\nfunc cmdStatus(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n\tif len(args) < 1 {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche status <run-id>\\n\")\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\tresp, err := client.GetStatus(ctx, &pb.GetStatusRequest{RunId: args[0]})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\tfmt.Printf(\"Run:       %s\\n\", resp.RunId)\n\tif resp.Title != \"\" {\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Title:     %s\\n\", resp.Title)\n\t}\n\tfmt.Printf(\"Workflow:  %s\\n\", resp.WorkflowName)\n\tif resp.IsHost {\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Type:      host\\n\")\n\t} else {\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Type:      container\\n\")\n\t}\n\tfmt.Printf(\"State:     %s\\n\", resp.State)\n\tif resp.ContainerId != \"\" {\n\t\tcid := resp.ContainerId\n\t\tif len(cid) > 12 {\n\t\t\tcid = cid[:12]\n\t\t}\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Container: %s\\n\", cid)\n\t}\n\tif resp.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Error:     %s\\n\", resp.ErrorMessage)\n\t}\n\tfmt.Printf(\"Active:    %s\\n\", resp.CurrentStep)\n\tfor _, exec := range resp.StepExecutions {\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"  %s: %s (%s -> %s)\\n\", exec.StepName, exec.Result, exec.StartedAt, exec.CompletedAt)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc cmdList(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n\tvar all bool\n\tfor _, arg := range args {\n\t\tif arg == \"--all\" {\n\t\t\tall = true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tresp, err := client.ListRuns(ctx, &pb.ListRunsRequest{All: all})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\tif len(resp.Runs) == 0 {\n\t\tfmt.Println(\"No runs found.\")\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, run := range resp.Runs {\n\t\trunType := \"container\"\n\t\tif run.IsHost {\n\t\t\trunType = \"host\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tline := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s  %-20s  %-10s  %-9s\", run.RunId, run.WorkflowName, run.State, runType)\n\t\tif run.Title != \"\" {\n\t\t\tt := run.Title\n\t\t\tif len(t) > 40 {\n\t\t\t\tt = t[:37] + \"...\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tline += \"  \" + t\n\t\t}\n\t\tif run.ContainerId != \"\" {\n\t\t\tline += \"  \" + run.ContainerId\n\t\t}\n\t\tif run.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n\t\t\terrMsg := run.ErrorMessage\n\t\t\tif len(errMsg) > 60 {\n\t\t\t\terrMsg = errMsg[:57] + \"...\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tline += \"  \" + errMsg\n\t\t}\n\t\tfmt.Println(line)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc cmdLogs(client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n\tif len(args) < 1 {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\\n\")\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\tvar stepFilter, typeFilter string\n\tvar follow bool\n\trunID := args[0]\n\n\tfor i := 1; i < len(args); i++ {\n\t\tswitch args[i] {\n\t\tcase \"--step\":\n\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n\t\t\t\ti++\n\t\t\t\tstepFilter = args[i]\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"--type\":\n\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n\t\t\t\ti++\n\t\t\t\ttypeFilter = args[i]\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"--follow\", \"-f\":\n\t\t\tfollow = true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tif follow {\n\t\tcmdLogsFollow(runID)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Use background context — log output can be large\n\tstream, err := client.StreamLogs(context.Background(), &pb.StreamLogsRequest{\n\t\tRunId:    runID,\n\t\tStepName: stepFilter,\n\t\tLogType:  typeFilter,\n\t})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\tfor {\n\t\tentry, err := stream.Recv()\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif errors.Is(err, io.EOF) {\n\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error reading logs: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tswitch entry.Type {\n\t\tcase \"step_started\":\n\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s started ---\\n\", entry.StepName)\n\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"%s\\n\", entry.Message)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"step_completed\":\n\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s: %s ---\\n\", entry.StepName, entry.Result)\n\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"%s\\n\", entry.Message)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"run_completed\":\n\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"\\nRun result: %s\\n\", entry.Result)\n\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Error:      %s\\n\", entry.Message)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase \"full_log\":\n\t\t\tfmt.Print(string(logstream.ParseClaudeStream([]byte(entry.Message))))\n\t\tcase \"log\":\n\t\t\t// Live-streamed log line from an active run.\n\t\t\tfmt.Println(entry.Message)\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\t// Handles filtered log entries like \"script_log\", \"llm_log\", \"step_log\"\n\t\t\tif entry.StepName != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s ---\\n\", entry.StepName)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Print(string(logstream.ParseClaudeStream([]byte(entry.Message))))\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc cmdLogsFollow(runID string) {\n\t// Determine HTTP address from env\n\thttpAddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_HTTP\")\n\tif httpAddr == \"\" {\n\t\thttpAddr = \"localhost:8080\"\n\t}\n\t// Strip protocol prefix if present\n\thttpAddr = strings.TrimPrefix(httpAddr, \"http://\")\n\n\tsseURL := fmt.Sprintf(\"http://%s/api/runs/%s/stream\", httpAddr, runID)\n\treq, err := http.NewRequest(\"GET\", sseURL, nil)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\treq.Header.Set(\"Accept\", \"text/event-stream\")\n\n\tresp, err := http.DefaultClient.Do(req)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error connecting to SSE stream: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n\n\tif resp.StatusCode != 200 {\n\t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: HTTP %d: %s\\n\", resp.StatusCode, strings.TrimSpace(string(body)))\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(resp.Body)\n\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n\t\tline := scanner.Text()\n\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(line, \"event: done\") {\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t\tif !strings.HasPrefix(line, \"data: \") {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tdata := strings.TrimPrefix(line, \"data: \")\n\n\t\tvar entry struct {\n\t\t\tTimestamp string `json:\"timestamp\"`\n\t\t\tType      string `json:\"type\"`\n\t\t\tContent   string `json:\"content\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &entry); err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\t// Color-code by type\n\t\tswitch entry.Type {\n\t\tcase \"status\":\n\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"\\033[34m[%s] [%s] %s\\033[0m\\n\", entry.Timestamp, entry.Type, entry.Content)\n\t\tcase \"llm\":\n\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"\\033[32m[%s] [%s] %s\\033[0m\\n\", entry.Timestamp, entry.Type, entry.Content)\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"[%s] [%s] %s\\n\", entry.Timestamp, entry.Type, entry.Content)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc cmdStop(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n\tif len(args) < 1 {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche stop <run-id>\\n\")\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\t_, err := client.StopRun(ctx, &pb.StopRunRequest{RunId: args[0]})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tfmt.Printf(\"Stopped run: %s\\n\", args[0])\n}\n\nfunc cmdDelete(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n\tif len(args) < 1 {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\\n\")\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\n\t_, err := client.DeleteContainer(ctx, &pb.DeleteContainerRequest{Id: args[0]})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tfmt.Printf(\"Deleted container: %s\\n\", args[0])\n}\n\nfunc cmdLoop(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n\n\t// Check for \"stop\" subcommand\n\tif len(args) > 0 && args[0] == \"stop\" {\n\t\t_, err := client.DisableLoop(ctx, &pb.DisableLoopRequest{ProjectDir: cwd})\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t\t}\n\t\tfmt.Println(\"Orchestration loop stopped.\")\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Default: 0 means \"use config value\" (server reads .cloche/config.toml).\n\tvar maxConcurrent int32\n\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n\t\tswitch args[i] {\n\t\tcase \"--max\":\n\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n\t\t\t\ti++\n\t\t\t\tn, err := fmt.Sscanf(args[i], \"%d\", &maxConcurrent)\n\t\t\t\tif n != 1 || err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"invalid --max value: %s\\n\", args[i])\n\t\t\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t_, err := client.EnableLoop(ctx, &pb.EnableLoopRequest{\n\t\tProjectDir:    cwd,\n\t\tMaxConcurrent: maxConcurrent,\n\t})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tif maxConcurrent > 0 {\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Orchestration loop started (max_concurrent=%d).\\n\", maxConcurrent)\n\t} else {\n\t\tfmt.Println(\"Orchestration loop started (using config defaults).\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc cmdShutdown(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient) {\n\t_, err := client.Shutdown(ctx, &pb.ShutdownRequest{})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n\t\tos.Exit(1)\n\t}\n\tfmt.Println(\"Daemon shutting down.\")\n}\n","numLines":479,"startLine":1,"totalLines":479}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019HJommBwKs2n84aStukUWv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package web\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bufio\"\n     5→\t\"context\"\n     6→\t\"embed\"\n     7→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     8→\t\"fmt\"\n     9→\t\"html/template\"\n    10→\t\"io/fs\"\n    11→\t\"net/http\"\n    12→\t\"net/url\"\n    13→\t\"os\"\n    14→\t\"os/exec\"\n    15→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    16→\t\"regexp\"\n    17→\t\"sort\"\n    18→\t\"strconv\"\n    19→\t\"strings\"\n    20→\t\"time\"\n    21→\n    22→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    23→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n    24→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n    25→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    26→)\n    27→\n    28→// HandlerOption configures optional Handler dependencies.\n    29→type HandlerOption func(*Handler)\n    30→\n    31→// WithContainerLogger sets the container runtime for fetching live logs.\n    32→func WithContainerLogger(c ContainerLogger) HandlerOption {\n    33→\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\n    34→}\n    35→\n    36→// WithContainerManager sets a full container manager (logs, inspect, remove).\n    37→func WithContainerManager(c ContainerManager) HandlerOption {\n    38→\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\n    39→}\n    40→\n    41→// WithLogBroadcaster sets the log broadcaster for SSE streaming.\n    42→func WithLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) HandlerOption {\n    43→\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logBroadcast = b }\n    44→}\n    45→\n    46→// WithLogStore sets the log store for indexed log file lookups.\n    47→func WithLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) HandlerOption {\n    48→\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logStore = ls }\n    49→}\n    50→\n    51→//go:embed templates/*.html static/*\n    52→var content embed.FS\n    53→\n    54→// Handler serves the web dashboard.\n    55→// ContainerLogger can retrieve logs from a container by ID.\n    56→type ContainerLogger interface {\n    57→\tLogs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→// ContainerManager extends ContainerLogger with container lifecycle operations.\n    61→type ContainerManager interface {\n    62→\tContainerLogger\n    63→\tStop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    64→\tRemove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    65→\tInspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ports.ContainerStatus, error)\n    66→}\n    67→\n    68→type Handler struct {\n    69→\tstore        ports.RunStore\n    70→\tcaptures     ports.CaptureStore\n    71→\tlogStore     ports.LogStore\n    72→\tcontainer    ContainerLogger\n    73→\tlogBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    74→\tpages        map[string]*template.Template\n    75→\tmux          *http.ServeMux\n    76→}\n    77→\n    78→// NewHandler creates a web dashboard handler.\n    79→func NewHandler(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, opts ...HandlerOption) (*Handler, error) {\n    80→\tfuncMap := template.FuncMap{\n    81→\t\t\"stateColor\":       stateColor,\n    82→\t\t\"healthColor\":      healthColor,\n    83→\t\t\"formatTime\":       formatTime,\n    84→\t\t\"formatDuration\":   formatDuration,\n    85→\t\t\"formatRunTiming\":  formatRunTiming,\n    86→\t\t\"truncate\":         truncate,\n    87→\t\t\"shortContainerID\": shortContainerID,\n    88→\t}\n    89→\n    90→\tbase, err := template.New(\"\").Funcs(funcMap).ParseFS(content, \"templates/layout.html\")\n    91→\tif err != nil {\n    92→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parse layout: %w\", err)\n    93→\t}\n    94→\n    95→\tpages := map[string]*template.Template{}\n    96→\tfor _, page := range []string{\"projects\", \"runs\", \"run_detail\", \"project_detail\"} {\n    97→\t\tclone, err := base.Clone()\n    98→\t\tif err != nil {\n    99→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"clone layout for %s: %w\", page, err)\n   100→\t\t}\n   101→\t\t_, err = clone.ParseFS(content, \"templates/\"+page+\".html\")\n   102→\t\tif err != nil {\n   103→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parse %s: %w\", page, err)\n   104→\t\t}\n   105→\t\tpages[page] = clone\n   106→\t}\n   107→\n   108→\th := &Handler{\n   109→\t\tstore:    store,\n   110→\t\tcaptures: captures,\n   111→\t\tpages:    pages,\n   112→\t\tmux:      http.NewServeMux(),\n   113→\t}\n   114→\tfor _, opt := range opts {\n   115→\t\topt(h)\n   116→\t}\n   117→\n   118→\tstaticFS, err := fs.Sub(content, \"static\")\n   119→\tif err != nil {\n   120→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"static sub-fs: %w\", err)\n   121→\t}\n   122→\n   123→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /{$}\", h.handleProjectOverview)\n   124→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}/runs\", h.handleProjectRuns)\n   125→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs\", h.handleRunsList)\n   126→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs/{id}\", h.handleRunDetail)\n   127→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}\", h.handleProjectDetail)\n   128→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects\", h.handleAPIProjects)\n   129→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs\", h.handleAPIRuns)\n   130→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}\", h.handleAPIRunDetail)\n   131→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\", h.handleAPIStepOutput)\n   132→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"POST /api/runs/{id}/stop\", h.handleAPIStopRun)\n   133→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container\", h.handleAPIDeleteContainer)\n   134→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"DELETE /api/projects/{name}/containers\", h.handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers)\n   135→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info\", h.handleAPIProjectInfo)\n   136→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff\", h.handleAPIPromptDiff)\n   137→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\", h.handleAPIWorkflows)\n   138→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\", h.handleAPIStepContent)\n   139→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}/stream\", h.handleAPIStream)\n   140→\th.mux.Handle(\"GET /static/\", http.StripPrefix(\"/static/\", http.FileServerFS(staticFS)))\n   141→\n   142→\treturn h, nil\n   143→}\n   144→\n   145→func (h *Handler) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   146→\th.mux.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n   147→}\n   148→\n   149→// --- HTML handlers ---\n   150→\n   151→// projectOverviewEntry holds data for a single project card on the landing page.\n   152→type projectOverviewEntry struct {\n   153→\tDir         string\n   154→\tLabel       string\n   155→\tHealth      domain.HealthResult\n   156→\tRecentRuns  []recentRunDot\n   157→\tActiveCount int\n   158→}\n   159→\n   160→// recentRunDot is a minimal representation of a run for the mini history display.\n   161→type recentRunDot struct {\n   162→\tID    string\n   163→\tState string\n   164→}\n   165→\n   166→const healthWindowSize = 10\n   167→\n   168→func (h *Handler) handleProjectOverview(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   169→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   170→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   171→\n   172→\tvar entries []projectOverviewEntry\n   173→\tfor _, dir := range projects {\n   174→\t\truns, err := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n   175→\t\tif err != nil {\n   176→\t\t\tcontinue\n   177→\t\t}\n   178→\n   179→\t\t// Convert []*domain.Run to []domain.Run for CalculateHealth.\n   180→\t\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\n   181→\t\tfor i, rr := range runs {\n   182→\t\t\trunValues[i] = *rr\n   183→\t\t}\n   184→\n   185→\t\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\n   186→\n   187→\t\t// Take the last N runs for the mini history (most recent first).\n   188→\t\tn := healthWindowSize\n   189→\t\tif n > len(runs) {\n   190→\t\t\tn = len(runs)\n   191→\t\t}\n   192→\t\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\n   193→\t\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n   194→\t\t\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{\n   195→\t\t\t\tID:    runs[i].ID,\n   196→\t\t\t\tState: string(runs[i].State),\n   197→\t\t\t}\n   198→\t\t}\n   199→\n   200→\t\tvar activeCount int\n   201→\t\tfor _, rr := range runs {\n   202→\t\t\tif rr.State == domain.RunStatePending || rr.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n   203→\t\t\t\tactiveCount++\n   204→\t\t\t}\n   205→\t\t}\n   206→\n   207→\t\tentries = append(entries, projectOverviewEntry{\n   208→\t\t\tDir:         dir,\n   209→\t\t\tLabel:       labels[dir],\n   210→\t\t\tHealth:      health,\n   211→\t\t\tRecentRuns:  dots,\n   212→\t\t\tActiveCount: activeCount,\n   213→\t\t})\n   214→\t}\n   215→\n   216→\tsort.Slice(entries, func(i, j int) bool {\n   217→\t\treturn entries[i].Label < entries[j].Label\n   218→\t})\n   219→\n   220→\tdata := map[string]any{\n   221→\t\t\"Title\":    \"Projects\",\n   222→\t\t\"Projects\": entries,\n   223→\t}\n   224→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n   225→\tif err := h.pages[\"projects\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n   226→\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   227→\t}\n   228→}\n   229→\n   230→func (h *Handler) handleRunsList(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   231→\tprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n   232→\n   233→\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n   234→\tvar err error\n   235→\tif projectFilter != \"\" {\n   236→\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n   237→\t} else {\n   238→\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n   239→\t}\n   240→\tif err != nil {\n   241→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list runs\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   242→\t\treturn\n   243→\t}\n   244→\n   245→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   246→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   247→\n   248→\t// Count retained containers per project\n   249→\tcontainerCounts := map[string]int{}\n   250→\tallRuns, _ := h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n   251→\tfor _, run := range allRuns {\n   252→\t\tif run.ContainerKept {\n   253→\t\t\tcontainerCounts[run.ProjectDir]++\n   254→\t\t}\n   255→\t}\n   256→\n   257→\tvar projectList []projectEntry\n   258→\tfor _, dir := range projects {\n   259→\t\tprojectList = append(projectList, projectEntry{Dir: dir, Label: labels[dir], ContainerCount: containerCounts[dir]})\n   260→\t}\n   261→\tsort.Slice(projectList, func(i, j int) bool {\n   262→\t\treturn projectList[i].Label < projectList[j].Label\n   263→\t})\n   264→\n   265→\tdata := map[string]any{\n   266→\t\t\"Title\":         \"Runs\",\n   267→\t\t\"Runs\":          runs,\n   268→\t\t\"Projects\":      projectList,\n   269→\t\t\"ProjectFilter\": projectFilter,\n   270→\t\t\"ProjectLabels\": labels,\n   271→\t}\n   272→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n   273→\tif err := h.pages[\"runs\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n   274→\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   275→\t}\n   276→}\n   277→\n   278→// handleProjectRuns redirects /projects/{name}/runs to /runs?project=<dir>.\n   279→func (h *Handler) handleProjectRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   280→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   281→\tif !ok {\n   282→\t\treturn\n   283→\t}\n   284→\thttp.Redirect(w, r, \"/runs?project=\"+url.QueryEscape(dir), http.StatusFound)\n   285→}\n   286→\n   287→// stepEntry is a merged view of a step execution for the template.\n   288→type stepEntry struct {\n   289→\tIndex     int\n   290→\tStepName  string\n   291→\tResult    string\n   292→\tStartedAt time.Time\n   293→\tDuration  string\n   294→}\n   295→\n   296→// mergeCaptures collapses started/completed capture pairs into single entries.\n   297→func mergeCaptures(caps []*domain.StepExecution) []stepEntry {\n   298→\tvar entries []stepEntry\n   299→\t// Track pending started rows by step name (LIFO for retries)\n   300→\tpending := map[string]*domain.StepExecution{}\n   301→\n   302→\tfor _, c := range caps {\n   303→\t\tif c.Result == \"\" {\n   304→\t\t\t// step_started row\n   305→\t\t\tpending[c.StepName] = c\n   306→\t\t\tcontinue\n   307→\t\t}\n   308→\t\t// step_completed row — merge with pending started if available\n   309→\t\tstartedAt := c.StartedAt\n   310→\t\tif started := pending[c.StepName]; started != nil {\n   311→\t\t\tstartedAt = started.StartedAt\n   312→\t\t\tdelete(pending, c.StepName)\n   313→\t\t}\n   314→\t\tentries = append(entries, stepEntry{\n   315→\t\t\tIndex:     len(entries),\n   316→\t\t\tStepName:  c.StepName,\n   317→\t\t\tResult:    c.Result,\n   318→\t\t\tStartedAt: startedAt,\n   319→\t\t\tDuration:  formatDuration(startedAt, c.CompletedAt),\n   320→\t\t})\n   321→\t}\n   322→\n   323→\t// Append any started-but-not-completed steps (still running)\n   324→\tfor _, c := range caps {\n   325→\t\tif c.Result == \"\" {\n   326→\t\t\tif _, used := pending[c.StepName]; !used {\n   327→\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   328→\t\t\t}\n   329→\t\t\tentries = append(entries, stepEntry{\n   330→\t\t\t\tIndex:     len(entries),\n   331→\t\t\t\tStepName:  c.StepName,\n   332→\t\t\t\tStartedAt: c.StartedAt,\n   333→\t\t\t})\n   334→\t\t\tdelete(pending, c.StepName)\n   335→\t\t}\n   336→\t}\n   337→\n   338→\treturn entries\n   339→}\n   340→\n   341→// containerState inspects the container for a run and returns one of:\n   342→//   - \"running\"   – container exists and is running\n   343→//   - \"stopped\"   – container exists, not running, not kept\n   344→//   - \"available\" – container exists, not running, kept (can be deleted)\n   345→//   - \"removed\"   – no container ID, no manager, or inspect failed\n   346→func (h *Handler) containerState(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) string {\n   347→\tif run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   348→\t\treturn \"removed\"\n   349→\t}\n   350→\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n   351→\tif !ok {\n   352→\t\treturn \"removed\"\n   353→\t}\n   354→\tstatus, err := mgr.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID)\n   355→\tif err != nil {\n   356→\t\treturn \"removed\"\n   357→\t}\n   358→\tif status.Running {\n   359→\t\treturn \"running\"\n   360→\t}\n   361→\tif run.ContainerKept {\n   362→\t\treturn \"available\"\n   363→\t}\n   364→\treturn \"stopped\"\n   365→}\n   366→\n   367→func (h *Handler) handleRunDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   368→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   369→\n   370→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   371→\tif err != nil {\n   372→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   373→\t\treturn\n   374→\t}\n   375→\n   376→\tcaps, err := h.captures.GetCaptures(r.Context(), id)\n   377→\tif err != nil {\n   378→\t\tcaps = nil // non-fatal\n   379→\t}\n   380→\n   381→\tsteps := mergeCaptures(caps)\n   382→\n   383→\t// Fetch parent run if this is a child\n   384→\tvar parentRun *domain.Run\n   385→\tif run.ParentRunID != \"\" {\n   386→\t\tparentRun, _ = h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), run.ParentRunID)\n   387→\t}\n   388→\n   389→\t// Fetch child runs\n   390→\tchildRuns, _ := h.store.ListChildRuns(r.Context(), id)\n   391→\n   392→\tdata := map[string]any{\n   393→\t\t\"Title\":          \"Run \" + run.ID,\n   394→\t\t\"Run\":            run,\n   395→\t\t\"Steps\":          steps,\n   396→\t\t\"Page\":           \"detail\",\n   397→\t\t\"ContainerState\": h.containerState(r.Context(), run),\n   398→\t\t\"ParentRun\":      parentRun,\n   399→\t\t\"ChildRuns\":      childRuns,\n   400→\t}\n   401→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n   402→\tif err := h.pages[\"run_detail\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n   403→\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   404→\t}\n   405→}\n   406→\n   407→// --- JSON API handlers ---\n   408→\n   409→type apiRun struct {\n   410→\tID           string `json:\"id\"`\n   411→\tWorkflowName string `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n   412→\tProjectDir   string `json:\"project_dir\"`\n   413→\tProjectLabel string `json:\"project_label\"`\n   414→\tState        string `json:\"state\"`\n   415→\tStartedAt    string `json:\"started_at\"`\n   416→\tCompletedAt  string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n   417→\tTiming       string `json:\"timing\"`\n   418→\tContainerID  string `json:\"container_id\"`\n   419→\tErrorMessage string `json:\"error_message\"`\n   420→\tTitle        string `json:\"title\"`\n   421→\tIsHost       bool   `json:\"is_host\"`\n   422→\tParentRunID  string `json:\"parent_run_id,omitempty\"`\n   423→}\n   424→\n   425→type apiStep struct {\n   426→\tStepName    string `json:\"step_name\"`\n   427→\tResult      string `json:\"result\"`\n   428→\tStartedAt   string `json:\"started_at\"`\n   429→\tCompletedAt string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n   430→\tDuration    string `json:\"duration\"`\n   431→}\n   432→\n   433→type apiRunDetail struct {\n   434→\tapiRun\n   435→\tContainerState string    `json:\"container_state\"`\n   436→\tSteps          []apiStep `json:\"steps\"`\n   437→\tChildRuns      []apiRun  `json:\"child_runs,omitempty\"`\n   438→}\n   439→\n   440→func toAPIRun(r *domain.Run, labels map[string]string) apiRun {\n   441→\treturn apiRun{\n   442→\t\tID:           r.ID,\n   443→\t\tWorkflowName: r.WorkflowName,\n   444→\t\tProjectDir:   r.ProjectDir,\n   445→\t\tProjectLabel: labels[r.ProjectDir],\n   446→\t\tState:        string(r.State),\n   447→\t\tStartedAt:    formatTime(r.StartedAt),\n   448→\t\tCompletedAt:  formatTime(r.CompletedAt),\n   449→\t\tTiming:       formatRunTiming(r.State, r.StartedAt, r.CompletedAt),\n   450→\t\tContainerID:  r.ContainerID,\n   451→\t\tErrorMessage: r.ErrorMessage,\n   452→\t\tTitle:        r.Title,\n   453→\t\tIsHost:       r.IsHost,\n   454→\t\tParentRunID:  r.ParentRunID,\n   455→\t}\n   456→}\n   457→\n   458→func (h *Handler) handleAPIRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   459→\tprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n   460→\n   461→\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n   462→\tvar err error\n   463→\tif projectFilter != \"\" {\n   464→\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n   465→\t} else {\n   466→\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n   467→\t}\n   468→\tif err != nil {\n   469→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list runs\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   470→\t\treturn\n   471→\t}\n   472→\n   473→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   474→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   475→\n   476→\tresult := make([]apiRun, len(runs))\n   477→\tfor i, run := range runs {\n   478→\t\tresult[i] = toAPIRun(run, labels)\n   479→\t}\n   480→\n   481→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   482→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(result)\n   483→}\n   484→\n   485→func (h *Handler) handleAPIProjects(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   486→\tprojects, err := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   487→\tif err != nil {\n   488→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list projects\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   489→\t\treturn\n   490→\t}\n   491→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   492→\n   493→\ttype apiHealth struct {\n   494→\t\tStatus string `json:\"status\"`\n   495→\t\tPassed int    `json:\"passed\"`\n   496→\t\tFailed int    `json:\"failed\"`\n   497→\t\tTotal  int    `json:\"total\"`\n   498→\t}\n   499→\ttype apiProject struct {\n   500→\t\tDir         string    `json:\"dir\"`\n   501→\t\tLabel       string    `json:\"label\"`\n   502→\t\tHealth      apiHealth `json:\"health\"`\n   503→\t\tActiveCount int       `json:\"active_count\"`\n   504→\t}\n   505→\tresult := make([]apiProject, len(projects))\n   506→\tfor i, dir := range projects {\n   507→\t\truns, _ := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n   508→\t\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\n   509→\t\tfor j, rr := range runs {\n   510→\t\t\trunValues[j] = *rr\n   511→\t\t}\n   512→\t\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\n   513→\t\tvar activeCount int\n   514→\t\tfor _, rr := range runs {\n   515→\t\t\tif rr.State == domain.RunStatePending || rr.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n   516→\t\t\t\tactiveCount++\n   517→\t\t\t}\n   518→\t\t}\n   519→\t\tresult[i] = apiProject{\n   520→\t\t\tDir:   dir,\n   521→\t\t\tLabel: labels[dir],\n   522→\t\t\tHealth: apiHealth{\n   523→\t\t\t\tStatus: string(health.Status),\n   524→\t\t\t\tPassed: health.Passed,\n   525→\t\t\t\tFailed: health.Failed,\n   526→\t\t\t\tTotal:  health.Total,\n   527→\t\t\t},\n   528→\t\t\tActiveCount: activeCount,\n   529→\t\t}\n   530→\t}\n   531→\n   532→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   533→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(result)\n   534→}\n   535→\n   536→func (h *Handler) handleAPIRunDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   537→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   538→\n   539→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   540→\tif err != nil {\n   541→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   542→\t\treturn\n   543→\t}\n   544→\n   545→\tcaps, err := h.captures.GetCaptures(r.Context(), id)\n   546→\tif err != nil {\n   547→\t\tcaps = nil\n   548→\t}\n   549→\n   550→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   551→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   552→\n   553→\tmerged := mergeCaptures(caps)\n   554→\tsteps := make([]apiStep, len(merged))\n   555→\tfor i, e := range merged {\n   556→\t\tsteps[i] = apiStep{\n   557→\t\t\tStepName:  e.StepName,\n   558→\t\t\tResult:    e.Result,\n   559→\t\t\tStartedAt: formatTime(e.StartedAt),\n   560→\t\t\tDuration:  e.Duration,\n   561→\t\t}\n   562→\t}\n   563→\n   564→\t// Fetch child runs for the API response\n   565→\tvar apiChildren []apiRun\n   566→\tif children, err := h.store.ListChildRuns(r.Context(), id); err == nil {\n   567→\t\tfor _, c := range children {\n   568→\t\t\tapiChildren = append(apiChildren, toAPIRun(c, labels))\n   569→\t\t}\n   570→\t}\n   571→\n   572→\tdetail := apiRunDetail{\n   573→\t\tapiRun:         toAPIRun(run, labels),\n   574→\t\tContainerState: h.containerState(r.Context(), run),\n   575→\t\tSteps:          steps,\n   576→\t\tChildRuns:      apiChildren,\n   577→\t}\n   578→\n   579→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   580→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(detail)\n   581→}\n   582→\n   583→func (h *Handler) handleAPIStepOutput(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   584→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   585→\tstep := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n   586→\tlogType := r.URL.Query().Get(\"type\")   // optional: \"script\", \"llm\"\n   587→\tformat := r.URL.Query().Get(\"format\")  // optional: \"raw\" to skip parsing\n   588→\n   589→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   590→\tif err != nil {\n   591→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   592→\t\treturn\n   593→\t}\n   594→\n   595→\twriteOutput := func(data []byte) {\n   596→\t\tif format != \"raw\" {\n   597→\t\t\tdata = logstream.ParseClaudeStream(data)\n   598→\t\t}\n   599→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n   600→\t\tw.Write(data)\n   601→\t}\n   602→\n   603→\t// Try log index first for fast lookup\n   604→\tif h.logStore != nil {\n   605→\t\tlogFiles, err := h.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(r.Context(), id, step)\n   606→\t\tif err == nil && len(logFiles) > 0 {\n   607→\t\t\t// If type filter specified, narrow results\n   608→\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n   609→\t\t\t\tif logType != \"\" && lf.FileType != logType {\n   610→\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   611→\t\t\t\t}\n   612→\t\t\t\tdata, readErr := os.ReadFile(lf.FilePath)\n   613→\t\t\t\tif readErr == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   614→\t\t\t\t\twriteOutput(data)\n   615→\t\t\t\t\treturn\n   616→\t\t\t\t}\n   617→\t\t\t}\n   618→\t\t}\n   619→\t}\n   620→\n   621→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", id, \"output\")\n   622→\n   623→\t// Fall back to file path conventions\n   624→\t// If type is \"llm\", try llm-<step>.log\n   625→\tif logType == \"llm\" {\n   626→\t\tllmPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, \"llm-\"+step+\".log\")\n   627→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(llmPath)\n   628→\t\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   629→\t\t\twriteOutput(data)\n   630→\t\t\treturn\n   631→\t\t}\n   632→\t}\n   633→\n   634→\t// Try per-step output file\n   635→\toutputPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, step+\".log\")\n   636→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath)\n   637→\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   638→\t\twriteOutput(data)\n   639→\t\treturn\n   640→\t}\n   641→\n   642→\t// Do NOT fall back to container.log or live docker logs here — those\n   643→\t// contain unfiltered output from ALL steps and would show the wrong\n   644→\t// content for this specific step (the root cause of web-UI log mismatches).\n   645→\n   646→\thttp.Error(w, \"step output not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   647→}\n   648→\n   649→func (h *Handler) handleAPIStopRun(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   650→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   651→\n   652→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   653→\tif err != nil {\n   654→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   655→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n   656→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run not found\"})\n   657→\t\treturn\n   658→\t}\n   659→\n   660→\t// Only allow stopping active runs\n   661→\tif run.State != domain.RunStatePending && run.State != domain.RunStateRunning {\n   662→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   663→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n   664→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run is not active\"})\n   665→\t\treturn\n   666→\t}\n   667→\n   668→\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n   669→\tif !ok || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   670→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   671→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n   672→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})\n   673→\t\treturn\n   674→\t}\n   675→\n   676→\tif err := mgr.Stop(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); err != nil {\n   677→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   678→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   679→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to stop run: %v\", err)})\n   680→\t\treturn\n   681→\t}\n   682→\n   683→\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateCancelled)\n   684→\tif err := h.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run); err != nil {\n   685→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   686→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   687→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to update run: %v\", err)})\n   688→\t\treturn\n   689→\t}\n   690→\n   691→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   692→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n   693→}\n   694→\n   695→func (h *Handler) handleAPIDeleteContainer(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   696→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   697→\n   698→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   699→\tif err != nil {\n   700→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   701→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n   702→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run not found\"})\n   703→\t\treturn\n   704→\t}\n   705→\n   706→\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n   707→\tif !ok || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   708→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   709→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n   710→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})\n   711→\t\treturn\n   712→\t}\n   713→\n   714→\tif err := mgr.Remove(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); err != nil {\n   715→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   716→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   717→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to remove container: %v\", err)})\n   718→\t\treturn\n   719→\t}\n   720→\n   721→\trun.ContainerKept = false\n   722→\tif err := h.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run); err != nil {\n   723→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   724→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   725→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to update run: %v\", err)})\n   726→\t\treturn\n   727→\t}\n   728→\n   729→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   730→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n   731→}\n   732→\n   733→// handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers mass-deletes all retained/exited containers for a project.\n   734→func (h *Handler) handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   735→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   736→\tif !ok {\n   737→\t\treturn\n   738→\t}\n   739→\n   740→\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n   741→\tif !ok {\n   742→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   743→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n   744→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})\n   745→\t\treturn\n   746→\t}\n   747→\n   748→\truns, err := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n   749→\tif err != nil {\n   750→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   751→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   752→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"failed to list runs\"})\n   753→\t\treturn\n   754→\t}\n   755→\n   756→\tvar deleted int\n   757→\tvar errors []string\n   758→\tfor _, run := range runs {\n   759→\t\tif !run.ContainerKept || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   760→\t\t\tcontinue\n   761→\t\t}\n   762→\t\t// Check container is not running\n   763→\t\tstatus, err := mgr.Inspect(r.Context(), run.ContainerID)\n   764→\t\tif err != nil {\n   765→\t\t\t// Container already gone — just clear the flag\n   766→\t\t\trun.ContainerKept = false\n   767→\t\t\th.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run)\n   768→\t\t\tdeleted++\n   769→\t\t\tcontinue\n   770→\t\t}\n   771→\t\tif status.Running {\n   772→\t\t\tcontinue // skip running containers\n   773→\t\t}\n   774→\t\tif err := mgr.Remove(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); err != nil {\n   775→\t\t\terrors = append(errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", run.ID, err))\n   776→\t\t\tcontinue\n   777→\t\t}\n   778→\t\trun.ContainerKept = false\n   779→\t\tif err := h.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run); err != nil {\n   780→\t\t\terrors = append(errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: update failed: %v\", run.ID, err))\n   781→\t\t\tcontinue\n   782→\t\t}\n   783→\t\tdeleted++\n   784→\t}\n   785→\n   786→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   787→\tresp := map[string]any{\"deleted\": deleted}\n   788→\tif len(errors) > 0 {\n   789→\t\tresp[\"errors\"] = errors\n   790→\t}\n   791→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n   792→}\n   793→\n   794→// handleAPIStream serves an SSE stream of log lines for a run.\n   795→// For active runs, it subscribes to the live broadcaster.\n   796→// For completed runs, it serves the archived full.log then closes.\n   797→func (h *Handler) handleAPIStream(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   798→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   799→\n   800→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   801→\tif err != nil {\n   802→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   803→\t\treturn\n   804→\t}\n   805→\n   806→\tflusher, ok := w.(http.Flusher)\n   807→\tif !ok {\n   808→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"streaming not supported\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   809→\t\treturn\n   810→\t}\n   811→\n   812→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/event-stream\")\n   813→\tw.Header().Set(\"Cache-Control\", \"no-cache\")\n   814→\tw.Header().Set(\"Connection\", \"keep-alive\")\n   815→\tw.Header().Set(\"X-Accel-Buffering\", \"no\")\n   816→\n   817→\tisComplete := run.State == domain.RunStateSucceeded ||\n   818→\t\trun.State == domain.RunStateFailed ||\n   819→\t\trun.State == domain.RunStateCancelled\n   820→\n   821→\tif isComplete {\n   822→\t\t// Serve archived full.log\n   823→\t\th.streamFullLog(w, flusher, run)\n   824→\t\t// Send done event\n   825→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"event: done\\ndata: %s\\n\\n\", string(run.State))\n   826→\t\tflusher.Flush()\n   827→\t\treturn\n   828→\t}\n   829→\n   830→\t// Active run: subscribe to live broadcaster\n   831→\tif h.logBroadcast == nil {\n   832→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"log streaming not available\", http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n   833→\t\treturn\n   834→\t}\n   835→\n   836→\tsub := h.logBroadcast.Subscribe(id)\n   837→\tdefer h.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(id, sub)\n   838→\n   839→\tctx := r.Context()\n   840→\tfor {\n   841→\t\tselect {\n   842→\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n   843→\t\t\treturn\n   844→\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n   845→\t\t\tif !ok {\n   846→\t\t\t\t// Stream finished (run completed)\n   847→\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"event: done\\ndata: completed\\n\\n\")\n   848→\t\t\t\tflusher.Flush()\n   849→\t\t\t\treturn\n   850→\t\t\t}\n   851→\t\t\tline = parseLLMLogLine(line)\n   852→\t\t\tif line.Type == \"\" {\n   853→\t\t\t\tcontinue // skip protocol-only llm lines\n   854→\t\t\t}\n   855→\t\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(line)\n   856→\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"data: %s\\n\\n\", data)\n   857→\t\t\tflusher.Flush()\n   858→\t\t}\n   859→\t}\n   860→}\n   861→\n   862→// logLineRegex parses \"[timestamp] [type] content\" format from full.log.\n   863→var logLineRegex = regexp.MustCompile(`^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`)\n   864→\n   865→// streamFullLog reads the archived full.log file and sends its entries as SSE events.\n   866→// LLM-type lines are parsed from raw Claude JSON into human-readable text.\n   867→func (h *Handler) streamFullLog(w http.ResponseWriter, flusher http.Flusher, run *domain.Run) {\n   868→\tlogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", run.ID, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n   869→\tf, err := os.Open(logPath)\n   870→\tif err != nil {\n   871→\t\treturn\n   872→\t}\n   873→\tdefer f.Close()\n   874→\n   875→\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(f)\n   876→\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n   877→\t\ttext := scanner.Text()\n   878→\t\tline := parseFullLogLine(text)\n   879→\t\tline = parseLLMLogLine(line)\n   880→\t\tif line.Type == \"\" {\n   881→\t\t\tcontinue // skip protocol-only llm lines\n   882→\t\t}\n   883→\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(line)\n   884→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"data: %s\\n\\n\", data)\n   885→\t\tflusher.Flush()\n   886→\t}\n   887→}\n   888→\n   889→// parseLLMLogLine parses a LogLine whose type is \"llm\". If the content is\n   890→// Claude stream JSON, it extracts the human-readable text. Protocol-only\n   891→// events return a LogLine with an empty Type (caller should skip it).\n   892→// Non-llm lines are returned unchanged.\n   893→func parseLLMLogLine(line logstream.LogLine) logstream.LogLine {\n   894→\tif line.Type != \"llm\" {\n   895→\t\treturn line\n   896→\t}\n   897→\ttext, ok := logstream.ParseClaudeLine([]byte(line.Content))\n   898→\tif !ok {\n   899→\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{} // signal to skip\n   900→\t}\n   901→\tline.Content = text\n   902→\treturn line\n   903→}\n   904→\n   905→// parseFullLogLine parses a \"[timestamp] [type] content\" line into a LogLine.\n   906→func parseFullLogLine(text string) logstream.LogLine {\n   907→\tm := logLineRegex.FindStringSubmatch(text)\n   908→\tif m == nil {\n   909→\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n   910→\t\t\tTimestamp: time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339),\n   911→\t\t\tType:      \"script\",\n   912→\t\t\tContent:   text,\n   913→\t\t}\n   914→\t}\n   915→\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n   916→\t\tTimestamp: m[1],\n   917→\t\tType:      m[2],\n   918→\t\tContent:   m[3],\n   919→\t}\n   920→}\n   921→\n   922→// --- Project detail handlers ---\n   923→\n   924→// resolveProjectDir resolves a project label from the URL to its directory path.\n   925→// Returns (dir, label, ok). Writes a JSON error response if not found.\n   926→func (h *Handler) resolveProjectDir(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) (string, string, bool) {\n   927→\tlabel := r.PathValue(\"name\")\n   928→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   929→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   930→\tfor dir, l := range labels {\n   931→\t\tif l == label {\n   932→\t\t\treturn dir, label, true\n   933→\t\t}\n   934→\t}\n   935→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   936→\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n   937→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"project not found\"})\n   938→\treturn \"\", \"\", false\n   939→}\n   940→\n   941→func (h *Handler) handleProjectDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   942→\tdir, label, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   943→\tif !ok {\n   944→\t\treturn\n   945→\t}\n   946→\n   947→\truns, _ := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n   948→\tn := 10\n   949→\tif n > len(runs) {\n   950→\t\tn = len(runs)\n   951→\t}\n   952→\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\n   953→\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n   954→\t\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{ID: runs[i].ID, State: string(runs[i].State)}\n   955→\t}\n   956→\n   957→\tvar containerCount int\n   958→\tfor _, run := range runs {\n   959→\t\tif run.ContainerKept {\n   960→\t\t\tcontainerCount++\n   961→\t\t}\n   962→\t}\n   963→\n   964→\tdata := map[string]any{\n   965→\t\t\"Title\":          label,\n   966→\t\t\"Label\":          label,\n   967→\t\t\"Dir\":            dir,\n   968→\t\t\"RecentRuns\":     dots,\n   969→\t\t\"ContainerCount\": containerCount,\n   970→\t}\n   971→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n   972→\tif err := h.pages[\"project_detail\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n   973→\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   974→\t}\n   975→}\n   976→\n   977→func (h *Handler) handleAPIProjectInfo(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   978→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   979→\tif !ok {\n   980→\t\treturn\n   981→\t}\n   982→\n   983→\t// Docker image: read FROM line from Dockerfile\n   984→\tdockerImage := \"\"\n   985→\tdockerfilePath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"Dockerfile\")\n   986→\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(dockerfilePath); err == nil {\n   987→\t\t// Find the last FROM line (final stage)\n   988→\t\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(string(data), \"\\n\") {\n   989→\t\t\ttrimmed := strings.TrimSpace(line)\n   990→\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(strings.ToUpper(trimmed), \"FROM \") {\n   991→\t\t\t\tparts := strings.Fields(trimmed)\n   992→\t\t\t\tif len(parts) >= 2 {\n   993→\t\t\t\t\tdockerImage = parts[1]\n   994→\t\t\t\t}\n   995→\t\t\t}\n   996→\t\t}\n   997→\t}\n   998→\n   999→\t// Version\n  1000→\tversion := 0\n  1001→\tversionPath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"version\")\n  1002→\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(versionPath); err == nil {\n  1003→\t\tif v, err := strconv.Atoi(strings.TrimSpace(string(data))); err == nil {\n  1004→\t\t\tversion = v\n  1005→\t\t}\n  1006→\t}\n  1007→\n  1008→\t// Prompt files history\n  1009→\ttype commitEntry struct {\n  1010→\t\tSHA     string `json:\"sha\"`\n  1011→\t\tDate    string `json:\"date\"`\n  1012→\t\tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n  1013→\t}\n  1014→\ttype promptFile struct {\n  1015→\t\tPath    string        `json:\"path\"`\n  1016→\t\tHistory []commitEntry `json:\"history\"`\n  1017→\t}\n  1018→\n  1019→\tvar promptFiles []promptFile\n  1020→\tpromptsDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"prompts\")\n  1021→\tif entries, err := os.ReadDir(promptsDir); err == nil {\n  1022→\t\tfor _, e := range entries {\n  1023→\t\t\tif e.IsDir() {\n  1024→\t\t\t\tcontinue\n  1025→\t\t\t}\n  1026→\t\t\trelPath := filepath.Join(\".cloche\", \"prompts\", e.Name())\n  1027→\t\t\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"log\", \"--follow\", \"--format=%H %aI %s\", \"--\", relPath)\n  1028→\t\t\tcmd.Dir = dir\n  1029→\t\t\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n  1030→\t\t\tif err != nil {\n  1031→\t\t\t\tcontinue\n  1032→\t\t\t}\n  1033→\t\t\tvar history []commitEntry\n  1034→\t\t\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(strings.TrimSpace(string(out)), \"\\n\") {\n  1035→\t\t\t\tif line == \"\" {\n  1036→\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n  1037→\t\t\t\t}\n  1038→\t\t\t\tparts := strings.SplitN(line, \" \", 3)\n  1039→\t\t\t\tif len(parts) < 3 {\n  1040→\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n  1041→\t\t\t\t}\n  1042→\t\t\t\t// Parse date to short form\n  1043→\t\t\t\tdateStr := parts[1]\n  1044→\t\t\t\tif t, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, dateStr); err == nil {\n  1045→\t\t\t\t\tdateStr = t.Format(\"2006-01-02\")\n  1046→\t\t\t\t}\n  1047→\t\t\t\thistory = append(history, commitEntry{\n  1048→\t\t\t\t\tSHA:     parts[0][:7],\n  1049→\t\t\t\t\tDate:    dateStr,\n  1050→\t\t\t\t\tMessage: parts[2],\n  1051→\t\t\t\t})\n  1052→\t\t\t}\n  1053→\t\t\tpromptFiles = append(promptFiles, promptFile{Path: relPath, History: history})\n  1054→\t\t}\n  1055→\t}\n  1056→\n  1057→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n  1058→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]any{\n  1059→\t\t\"docker_image\": dockerImage,\n  1060→\t\t\"version\":      version,\n  1061→\t\t\"prompt_files\": promptFiles,\n  1062→\t})\n  1063→}\n  1064→\n  1065→func (h *Handler) handleAPIPromptDiff(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n  1066→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n  1067→\tif !ok {\n  1068→\t\treturn\n  1069→\t}\n  1070→\tfile := r.URL.Query().Get(\"file\")\n  1071→\tsha := r.URL.Query().Get(\"sha\")\n  1072→\tif file == \"\" || sha == \"\" {\n  1073→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"file and sha required\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n  1074→\t\treturn\n  1075→\t}\n  1076→\n  1077→\t// Validate sha is alphanumeric to prevent injection\n  1078→\tfor _, c := range sha {\n  1079→\t\tif !((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')) {\n  1080→\t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"invalid sha\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n  1081→\t\t\treturn\n  1082→\t\t}\n  1083→\t}\n  1084→\n  1085→\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n  1086→\tcmd.Dir = dir\n  1087→\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n  1088→\tif err != nil {\n  1089→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"diff not available\", http.StatusNotFound)\n  1090→\t\treturn\n  1091→\t}\n  1092→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n  1093→\tw.Write(out)\n  1094→}\n  1095→\n  1096→func (h *Handler) handleAPIWorkflows(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n  1097→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n  1098→\tif !ok {\n  1099→\t\treturn\n  1100→\t}\n  1101→\n  1102→\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n  1103→\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n  1104→\tif err != nil {\n  1105→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n  1106→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode([]any{})\n  1107→\t\treturn\n  1108→\t}\n  1109→\n  1110→\ttype apiWire struct {\n  1111→\t\tFrom   string `json:\"from\"`\n  1112→\t\tResult string `json:\"result\"`\n  1113→\t\tTo     string `json:\"to\"`\n  1114→\t}\n  1115→\ttype apiStepDef struct {\n  1116→\t\tName    string            `json:\"name\"`\n  1117→\t\tType    string            `json:\"type\"`\n  1118→\t\tResults []string          `json:\"results\"`\n  1119→\t\tConfig  map[string]string `json:\"config\"`\n  1120→\t}\n  1121→\ttype apiWorkflow struct {\n  1122→\t\tName      string       `json:\"name\"`\n  1123→\t\tFile      string       `json:\"file\"`\n  1124→\t\tSteps     []apiStepDef `json:\"steps\"`\n  1125→\t\tWires     []apiWire    `json:\"wires\"`\n  1126→\t\tEntryStep string       `json:\"entry_step\"`\n  1127→\t}\n  1128→\n  1129→\tvar workflows []apiWorkflow\n  1130→\tfor _, e := range entries {\n  1131→\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n  1132→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1133→\t\t}\n  1134→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n  1135→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1136→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1137→\t\t}\n  1138→\t\twf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n  1139→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1140→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1141→\t\t}\n  1142→\t\tvar steps []apiStepDef\n  1143→\t\tfor _, s := range wf.Steps {\n  1144→\t\t\tsteps = append(steps, apiStepDef{\n  1145→\t\t\t\tName:    s.Name,\n  1146→\t\t\t\tType:    string(s.Type),\n  1147→\t\t\t\tResults: s.Results,\n  1148→\t\t\t\tConfig:  s.Config,\n  1149→\t\t\t})\n  1150→\t\t}\n  1151→\t\t// Sort steps by name for consistent ordering\n  1152→\t\tsort.Slice(steps, func(i, j int) bool { return steps[i].Name < steps[j].Name })\n  1153→\n  1154→\t\tvar wires []apiWire\n  1155→\t\tfor _, wire := range wf.Wiring {\n  1156→\t\t\twires = append(wires, apiWire{From: wire.From, Result: wire.Result, To: wire.To})\n  1157→\t\t}\n  1158→\n  1159→\t\tworkflows = append(workflows, apiWorkflow{\n  1160→\t\t\tName:      wf.Name,\n  1161→\t\t\tFile:      filepath.Join(\".cloche\", e.Name()),\n  1162→\t\t\tSteps:     steps,\n  1163→\t\t\tWires:     wires,\n  1164→\t\t\tEntryStep: wf.EntryStep,\n  1165→\t\t})\n  1166→\t}\n  1167→\n  1168→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n  1169→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(workflows)\n  1170→}\n  1171→\n  1172→func (h *Handler) handleAPIStepContent(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n  1173→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n  1174→\tif !ok {\n  1175→\t\treturn\n  1176→\t}\n  1177→\tworkflowName := r.PathValue(\"workflow\")\n  1178→\tstepName := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n  1179→\n  1180→\t// Find the workflow file\n  1181→\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n  1182→\tvar wf *domain.Workflow\n  1183→\tentries, _ := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n  1184→\tfor _, e := range entries {\n  1185→\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n  1186→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1187→\t\t}\n  1188→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n  1189→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1190→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1191→\t\t}\n  1192→\t\tparsed, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n  1193→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1194→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1195→\t\t}\n  1196→\t\tif parsed.Name == workflowName {\n  1197→\t\t\twf = parsed\n  1198→\t\t\tbreak\n  1199→\t\t}\n  1200→\t}\n  1201→\tif wf == nil {\n  1202→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"workflow not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n  1203→\t\treturn\n  1204→\t}\n  1205→\n  1206→\tstep, ok := wf.Steps[stepName]\n  1207→\tif !ok {\n  1208→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"step not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n  1209→\t\treturn\n  1210→\t}\n  1211→\n  1212→\t// Try to read the referenced file from step config\n  1213→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n  1214→\n  1215→\tif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n  1216→\t\tcontent, err := resolveFileRef(prompt, dir)\n  1217→\t\tif err == nil {\n  1218→\t\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n  1219→\t\t\treturn\n  1220→\t\t}\n  1221→\t}\n  1222→\tif cmd := step.Config[\"command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n  1223→\t\tcontent, _ := resolveFileRef(cmd, dir)\n  1224→\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n  1225→\t\treturn\n  1226→\t}\n  1227→\tif script := step.Config[\"script\"]; script != \"\" {\n  1228→\t\tcontent, _ := resolveFileRef(script, dir)\n  1229→\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n  1230→\t\treturn\n  1231→\t}\n  1232→\n  1233→\thttp.Error(w, \"no content available\", http.StatusNotFound)\n  1234→}\n  1235→\n  1236→// --- Template helpers ---\n  1237→\n  1238→// resolveFileRef resolves file(\"path\") DSL syntax to actual file contents.\n  1239→// If the value uses file() syntax, the referenced file is read from disk.\n  1240→// Otherwise the value is returned as-is.\n  1241→func resolveFileRef(value, baseDir string) (string, error) {\n  1242→\tif strings.HasPrefix(value, `file(\"`) && strings.HasSuffix(value, `\")`) {\n  1243→\t\tpath := value[6 : len(value)-2]\n  1244→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(baseDir, path))\n  1245→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1246→\t\t\treturn \"\", err\n  1247→\t\t}\n  1248→\t\treturn string(data), nil\n  1249→\t}\n  1250→\treturn value, nil\n  1251→}\n  1252→\n  1253→func stateColor(state domain.RunState) string {\n  1254→\tswitch state {\n  1255→\tcase domain.RunStatePending:\n  1256→\t\treturn \"pending\"\n  1257→\tcase domain.RunStateRunning:\n  1258→\t\treturn \"running\"\n  1259→\tcase domain.RunStateSucceeded:\n  1260→\t\treturn \"succeeded\"\n  1261→\tcase domain.RunStateFailed:\n  1262→\t\treturn \"failed\"\n  1263→\tcase domain.RunStateCancelled:\n  1264→\t\treturn \"cancelled\"\n  1265→\tdefault:\n  1266→\t\treturn \"pending\"\n  1267→\t}\n  1268→}\n  1269→\n  1270→func healthColor(status domain.HealthStatus) string {\n  1271→\tswitch status {\n  1272→\tcase domain.HealthGreen:\n  1273→\t\treturn \"green\"\n  1274→\tcase domain.HealthYellow:\n  1275→\t\treturn \"yellow\"\n  1276→\tcase domain.HealthRed:\n  1277→\t\treturn \"red\"\n  1278→\tcase domain.HealthBlue:\n  1279→\t\treturn \"blue\"\n  1280→\tdefault:\n  1281→\t\treturn \"grey\"\n  1282→\t}\n  1283→}\n  1284→\n  1285→func formatTime(t time.Time) string {\n  1286→\tif t.IsZero() {\n  1287→\t\treturn \"\"\n  1288→\t}\n  1289→\treturn t.Format(\"2006-01-02 15:04:05\")\n  1290→}\n  1291→\n  1292→func formatDuration(start, end time.Time) string {\n  1293→\tif start.IsZero() || end.IsZero() {\n  1294→\t\treturn \"\"\n  1295→\t}\n  1296→\td := end.Sub(start)\n  1297→\tif d < time.Second {\n  1298→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dms\", d.Milliseconds())\n  1299→\t}\n  1300→\tif d < time.Minute {\n  1301→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%.1fs\", d.Seconds())\n  1302→\t}\n  1303→\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dm%ds\", int(d.Minutes()), int(d.Seconds())%60)\n  1304→}\n  1305→\n  1306→// formatSmartDuration formats a duration into a human-friendly short string.\n  1307→// Examples: \"3s\", \"2m\", \"1h20m\", \"3h\".\n  1308→func formatSmartDuration(d time.Duration) string {\n  1309→\tif d < time.Minute {\n  1310→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%ds\", int(d.Seconds()))\n  1311→\t}\n  1312→\th := int(d.Hours())\n  1313→\tm := int(d.Minutes()) % 60\n  1314→\tif h == 0 {\n  1315→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dm\", m)\n  1316→\t}\n  1317→\tif m == 0 {\n  1318→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dh\", h)\n  1319→\t}\n  1320→\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dh%dm\", h, m)\n  1321→}\n  1322→\n  1323→// roundRelativeTime rounds a duration to neat display units:\n  1324→// <1m -> \"<1m ago\", then 1m,5m,10m,15m,30m,45m,1h,2h,3h,...24h,\n  1325→// then days.\n  1326→func roundRelativeTime(d time.Duration) string {\n  1327→\tif d < time.Minute {\n  1328→\t\treturn \"<1m ago\"\n  1329→\t}\n  1330→\tmins := int(d.Minutes())\n  1331→\thours := int(d.Hours())\n  1332→\tdays := hours / 24\n  1333→\n  1334→\tif days > 0 {\n  1335→\t\tif days == 1 {\n  1336→\t\t\treturn \"1 day ago\"\n  1337→\t\t}\n  1338→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%d days ago\", days)\n  1339→\t}\n  1340→\tif hours >= 1 {\n  1341→\t\tif hours == 1 {\n  1342→\t\t\treturn \"1 hour ago\"\n  1343→\t\t}\n  1344→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%d hours ago\", hours)\n  1345→\t}\n  1346→\t// Round minutes to neat breakpoints\n  1347→\tswitch {\n  1348→\tcase mins < 3:\n  1349→\t\treturn \"1m ago\"\n  1350→\tcase mins < 8:\n  1351→\t\treturn \"5m ago\"\n  1352→\tcase mins < 13:\n  1353→\t\treturn \"10m ago\"\n  1354→\tcase mins < 20:\n  1355→\t\treturn \"15m ago\"\n  1356→\tcase mins < 38:\n  1357→\t\treturn \"30m ago\"\n  1358→\tcase mins < 53:\n  1359→\t\treturn \"45m ago\"\n  1360→\tdefault:\n  1361→\t\treturn \"1 hour ago\"\n  1362→\t}\n  1363→}\n  1364→\n  1365→// formatRunTiming returns a smart timing string for display on the Runs page.\n  1366→// Running: \"5m\" (just duration so far)\n  1367→// Completed: \"20m, 1 hour ago\"\n  1368→// Pending: \"\"\n  1369→func formatRunTiming(state domain.RunState, startedAt, completedAt time.Time) string {\n  1370→\treturn formatRunTimingAt(state, startedAt, completedAt, time.Now())\n  1371→}\n  1372→\n  1373→// formatRunTimingAt is the testable version of formatRunTiming with an explicit \"now\".\n  1374→func formatRunTimingAt(state domain.RunState, startedAt, completedAt, now time.Time) string {\n  1375→\tif startedAt.IsZero() {\n  1376→\t\treturn \"\"\n  1377→\t}\n  1378→\tswitch state {\n  1379→\tcase domain.RunStateRunning:\n  1380→\t\td := now.Sub(startedAt)\n  1381→\t\treturn formatSmartDuration(d)\n  1382→\tdefault:\n  1383→\t\tif completedAt.IsZero() {\n  1384→\t\t\treturn \"\"\n  1385→\t\t}\n  1386→\t\td := completedAt.Sub(startedAt)\n  1387→\t\tago := now.Sub(completedAt)\n  1388→\t\treturn formatSmartDuration(d) + \", \" + roundRelativeTime(ago)\n  1389→\t}\n  1390→}\n  1391→\n  1392→func truncate(s string, n int) string {\n  1393→\tif len(s) <= n {\n  1394→\t\treturn s\n  1395→\t}\n  1396→\treturn s[:n] + \"...\"\n  1397→}\n  1398→\n  1399→func shortContainerID(id string) string {\n  1400→\tif len(id) > 12 {\n  1401→\t\treturn id[:12]\n  1402→\t}\n  1403→\treturn id\n  1404→}\n  1405→\n  1406→// projectLabels builds a mapping from full project directory paths to short\n  1407→// display labels. Each label is the final directory component (e.g.\n  1408→// \"myproject\" from \"/home/user/workspace/myproject\"). When two projects share\n  1409→// the same final name, the parent directory is prepended to disambiguate\n  1410→// (e.g. \"foo/bar\" vs \"baz/bar\").\n  1411→func projectLabels(dirs []string) map[string]string {\n  1412→\tlabels := make(map[string]string, len(dirs))\n  1413→\t// Group dirs by their base name to detect conflicts.\n  1414→\tbyBase := map[string][]string{}\n  1415→\tfor _, d := range dirs {\n  1416→\t\tbase := filepath.Base(d)\n  1417→\t\tbyBase[base] = append(byBase[base], d)\n  1418→\t}\n  1419→\tfor base, paths := range byBase {\n  1420→\t\tif len(paths) == 1 {\n  1421→\t\t\tlabels[paths[0]] = base\n  1422→\t\t} else {\n  1423→\t\t\tfor _, p := range paths {\n  1424→\t\t\t\tparent := filepath.Base(filepath.Dir(p))\n  1425→\t\t\t\tlabels[p] = parent + \"/\" + base\n  1426→\t\t\t}\n  1427→\t\t}\n  1428→\t}\n  1429→\treturn labels\n  1430→}\n  1431→\n  1432→type projectEntry struct {\n  1433→\tDir            string\n  1434→\tLabel          string\n  1435→\tContainerCount int\n  1436→}\n  1437→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6146b7bf-a511-4374-8899-2af97fce0332","uuid":"3636480d-7798-425e-a40c-52bd3f0241a2","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go","content":"package web\n\nimport (\n\t\"bufio\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"embed\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"html/template\"\n\t\"io/fs\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"net/url\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"os/exec\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"regexp\"\n\t\"sort\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n)\n\n// HandlerOption configures optional Handler dependencies.\ntype HandlerOption func(*Handler)\n\n// WithContainerLogger sets the container runtime for fetching live logs.\nfunc WithContainerLogger(c ContainerLogger) HandlerOption {\n\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\n}\n\n// WithContainerManager sets a full container manager (logs, inspect, remove).\nfunc WithContainerManager(c ContainerManager) HandlerOption {\n\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\n}\n\n// WithLogBroadcaster sets the log broadcaster for SSE streaming.\nfunc WithLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) HandlerOption {\n\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logBroadcast = b }\n}\n\n// WithLogStore sets the log store for indexed log file lookups.\nfunc WithLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) HandlerOption {\n\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logStore = ls }\n}\n\n//go:embed templates/*.html static/*\nvar content embed.FS\n\n// Handler serves the web dashboard.\n// ContainerLogger can retrieve logs from a container by ID.\ntype ContainerLogger interface {\n\tLogs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n}\n\n// ContainerManager extends ContainerLogger with container lifecycle operations.\ntype ContainerManager interface {\n\tContainerLogger\n\tStop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n\tRemove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n\tInspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ports.ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype Handler struct {\n\tstore        ports.RunStore\n\tcaptures     ports.CaptureStore\n\tlogStore     ports.LogStore\n\tcontainer    ContainerLogger\n\tlogBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n\tpages        map[string]*template.Template\n\tmux          *http.ServeMux\n}\n\n// NewHandler creates a web dashboard handler.\nfunc NewHandler(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, opts ...HandlerOption) (*Handler, error) {\n\tfuncMap := template.FuncMap{\n\t\t\"stateColor\":       stateColor,\n\t\t\"healthColor\":      healthColor,\n\t\t\"formatTime\":       formatTime,\n\t\t\"formatDuration\":   formatDuration,\n\t\t\"formatRunTiming\":  formatRunTiming,\n\t\t\"truncate\":         truncate,\n\t\t\"shortContainerID\": shortContainerID,\n\t}\n\n\tbase, err := template.New(\"\").Funcs(funcMap).ParseFS(content, \"templates/layout.html\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parse layout: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tpages := map[string]*template.Template{}\n\tfor _, page := range []string{\"projects\", \"runs\", \"run_detail\", \"project_detail\"} {\n\t\tclone, err := base.Clone()\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"clone layout for %s: %w\", page, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\t_, err = clone.ParseFS(content, \"templates/\"+page+\".html\")\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parse %s: %w\", page, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tpages[page] = clone\n\t}\n\n\th := &Handler{\n\t\tstore:    store,\n\t\tcaptures: captures,\n\t\tpages:    pages,\n\t\tmux:      http.NewServeMux(),\n\t}\n\tfor _, opt := range opts {\n\t\topt(h)\n\t}\n\n\tstaticFS, err := fs.Sub(content, \"static\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"static sub-fs: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /{$}\", h.handleProjectOverview)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}/runs\", h.handleProjectRuns)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs\", h.handleRunsList)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs/{id}\", h.handleRunDetail)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}\", h.handleProjectDetail)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects\", h.handleAPIProjects)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs\", h.handleAPIRuns)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}\", h.handleAPIRunDetail)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\", h.handleAPIStepOutput)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"POST /api/runs/{id}/stop\", h.handleAPIStopRun)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container\", h.handleAPIDeleteContainer)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"DELETE /api/projects/{name}/containers\", h.handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info\", h.handleAPIProjectInfo)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff\", h.handleAPIPromptDiff)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\", h.handleAPIWorkflows)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\", h.handleAPIStepContent)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}/stream\", h.handleAPIStream)\n\th.mux.Handle(\"GET /static/\", http.StripPrefix(\"/static/\", http.FileServerFS(staticFS)))\n\n\treturn h, nil\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\th.mux.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n}\n\n// --- HTML handlers ---\n\n// projectOverviewEntry holds data for a single project card on the landing page.\ntype projectOverviewEntry struct {\n\tDir         string\n\tLabel       string\n\tHealth      domain.HealthResult\n\tRecentRuns  []recentRunDot\n\tActiveCount int\n}\n\n// recentRunDot is a minimal representation of a run for the mini history display.\ntype recentRunDot struct {\n\tID    string\n\tState string\n}\n\nconst healthWindowSize = 10\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleProjectOverview(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\tvar entries []projectOverviewEntry\n\tfor _, dir := range projects {\n\t\truns, err := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\t// Convert []*domain.Run to []domain.Run for CalculateHealth.\n\t\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\n\t\tfor i, rr := range runs {\n\t\t\trunValues[i] = *rr\n\t\t}\n\n\t\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\n\n\t\t// Take the last N runs for the mini history (most recent first).\n\t\tn := healthWindowSize\n\t\tif n > len(runs) {\n\t\t\tn = len(runs)\n\t\t}\n\t\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\n\t\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n\t\t\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{\n\t\t\t\tID:    runs[i].ID,\n\t\t\t\tState: string(runs[i].State),\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tvar activeCount int\n\t\tfor _, rr := range runs {\n\t\t\tif rr.State == domain.RunStatePending || rr.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n\t\t\t\tactiveCount++\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tentries = append(entries, projectOverviewEntry{\n\t\t\tDir:         dir,\n\t\t\tLabel:       labels[dir],\n\t\t\tHealth:      health,\n\t\t\tRecentRuns:  dots,\n\t\t\tActiveCount: activeCount,\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\tsort.Slice(entries, func(i, j int) bool {\n\t\treturn entries[i].Label < entries[j].Label\n\t})\n\n\tdata := map[string]any{\n\t\t\"Title\":    \"Projects\",\n\t\t\"Projects\": entries,\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\tif err := h.pages[\"projects\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleRunsList(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n\n\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n\tvar err error\n\tif projectFilter != \"\" {\n\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n\t} else {\n\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n\t}\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list runs\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\t// Count retained containers per project\n\tcontainerCounts := map[string]int{}\n\tallRuns, _ := h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n\tfor _, run := range allRuns {\n\t\tif run.ContainerKept {\n\t\t\tcontainerCounts[run.ProjectDir]++\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tvar projectList []projectEntry\n\tfor _, dir := range projects {\n\t\tprojectList = append(projectList, projectEntry{Dir: dir, Label: labels[dir], ContainerCount: containerCounts[dir]})\n\t}\n\tsort.Slice(projectList, func(i, j int) bool {\n\t\treturn projectList[i].Label < projectList[j].Label\n\t})\n\n\tdata := map[string]any{\n\t\t\"Title\":         \"Runs\",\n\t\t\"Runs\":          runs,\n\t\t\"Projects\":      projectList,\n\t\t\"ProjectFilter\": projectFilter,\n\t\t\"ProjectLabels\": labels,\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\tif err := h.pages[\"runs\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t}\n}\n\n// handleProjectRuns redirects /projects/{name}/runs to /runs?project=<dir>.\nfunc (h *Handler) handleProjectRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\thttp.Redirect(w, r, \"/runs?project=\"+url.QueryEscape(dir), http.StatusFound)\n}\n\n// stepEntry is a merged view of a step execution for the template.\ntype stepEntry struct {\n\tIndex     int\n\tStepName  string\n\tResult    string\n\tStartedAt time.Time\n\tDuration  string\n}\n\n// mergeCaptures collapses started/completed capture pairs into single entries.\nfunc mergeCaptures(caps []*domain.StepExecution) []stepEntry {\n\tvar entries []stepEntry\n\t// Track pending started rows by step name (LIFO for retries)\n\tpending := map[string]*domain.StepExecution{}\n\n\tfor _, c := range caps {\n\t\tif c.Result == \"\" {\n\t\t\t// step_started row\n\t\t\tpending[c.StepName] = c\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\t// step_completed row — merge with pending started if available\n\t\tstartedAt := c.StartedAt\n\t\tif started := pending[c.StepName]; started != nil {\n\t\t\tstartedAt = started.StartedAt\n\t\t\tdelete(pending, c.StepName)\n\t\t}\n\t\tentries = append(entries, stepEntry{\n\t\t\tIndex:     len(entries),\n\t\t\tStepName:  c.StepName,\n\t\t\tResult:    c.Result,\n\t\t\tStartedAt: startedAt,\n\t\t\tDuration:  formatDuration(startedAt, c.CompletedAt),\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\t// Append any started-but-not-completed steps (still running)\n\tfor _, c := range caps {\n\t\tif c.Result == \"\" {\n\t\t\tif _, used := pending[c.StepName]; !used {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tentries = append(entries, stepEntry{\n\t\t\t\tIndex:     len(entries),\n\t\t\t\tStepName:  c.StepName,\n\t\t\t\tStartedAt: c.StartedAt,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t\tdelete(pending, c.StepName)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn entries\n}\n\n// containerState inspects the container for a run and returns one of:\n//   - \"running\"   – container exists and is running\n//   - \"stopped\"   – container exists, not running, not kept\n//   - \"available\" – container exists, not running, kept (can be deleted)\n//   - \"removed\"   – no container ID, no manager, or inspect failed\nfunc (h *Handler) containerState(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) string {\n\tif run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"removed\"\n\t}\n\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn \"removed\"\n\t}\n\tstatus, err := mgr.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"removed\"\n\t}\n\tif status.Running {\n\t\treturn \"running\"\n\t}\n\tif run.ContainerKept {\n\t\treturn \"available\"\n\t}\n\treturn \"stopped\"\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleRunDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tcaps, err := h.captures.GetCaptures(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tcaps = nil // non-fatal\n\t}\n\n\tsteps := mergeCaptures(caps)\n\n\t// Fetch parent run if this is a child\n\tvar parentRun *domain.Run\n\tif run.ParentRunID != \"\" {\n\t\tparentRun, _ = h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), run.ParentRunID)\n\t}\n\n\t// Fetch child runs\n\tchildRuns, _ := h.store.ListChildRuns(r.Context(), id)\n\n\tdata := map[string]any{\n\t\t\"Title\":          \"Run \" + run.ID,\n\t\t\"Run\":            run,\n\t\t\"Steps\":          steps,\n\t\t\"Page\":           \"detail\",\n\t\t\"ContainerState\": h.containerState(r.Context(), run),\n\t\t\"ParentRun\":      parentRun,\n\t\t\"ChildRuns\":      childRuns,\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\tif err := h.pages[\"run_detail\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t}\n}\n\n// --- JSON API handlers ---\n\ntype apiRun struct {\n\tID           string `json:\"id\"`\n\tWorkflowName string `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n\tProjectDir   string `json:\"project_dir\"`\n\tProjectLabel string `json:\"project_label\"`\n\tState        string `json:\"state\"`\n\tStartedAt    string `json:\"started_at\"`\n\tCompletedAt  string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n\tTiming       string `json:\"timing\"`\n\tContainerID  string `json:\"container_id\"`\n\tErrorMessage string `json:\"error_message\"`\n\tTitle        string `json:\"title\"`\n\tIsHost       bool   `json:\"is_host\"`\n\tParentRunID  string `json:\"parent_run_id,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype apiStep struct {\n\tStepName    string `json:\"step_name\"`\n\tResult      string `json:\"result\"`\n\tStartedAt   string `json:\"started_at\"`\n\tCompletedAt string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n\tDuration    string `json:\"duration\"`\n}\n\ntype apiRunDetail struct {\n\tapiRun\n\tContainerState string    `json:\"container_state\"`\n\tSteps          []apiStep `json:\"steps\"`\n\tChildRuns      []apiRun  `json:\"child_runs,omitempty\"`\n}\n\nfunc toAPIRun(r *domain.Run, labels map[string]string) apiRun {\n\treturn apiRun{\n\t\tID:           r.ID,\n\t\tWorkflowName: r.WorkflowName,\n\t\tProjectDir:   r.ProjectDir,\n\t\tProjectLabel: labels[r.ProjectDir],\n\t\tState:        string(r.State),\n\t\tStartedAt:    formatTime(r.StartedAt),\n\t\tCompletedAt:  formatTime(r.CompletedAt),\n\t\tTiming:       formatRunTiming(r.State, r.StartedAt, r.CompletedAt),\n\t\tContainerID:  r.ContainerID,\n\t\tErrorMessage: r.ErrorMessage,\n\t\tTitle:        r.Title,\n\t\tIsHost:       r.IsHost,\n\t\tParentRunID:  r.ParentRunID,\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n\n\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n\tvar err error\n\tif projectFilter != \"\" {\n\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n\t} else {\n\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n\t}\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list runs\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\tresult := make([]apiRun, len(runs))\n\tfor i, run := range runs {\n\t\tresult[i] = toAPIRun(run, labels)\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(result)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIProjects(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tprojects, err := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list projects\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\ttype apiHealth struct {\n\t\tStatus string `json:\"status\"`\n\t\tPassed int    `json:\"passed\"`\n\t\tFailed int    `json:\"failed\"`\n\t\tTotal  int    `json:\"total\"`\n\t}\n\ttype apiProject struct {\n\t\tDir         string    `json:\"dir\"`\n\t\tLabel       string    `json:\"label\"`\n\t\tHealth      apiHealth `json:\"health\"`\n\t\tActiveCount int       `json:\"active_count\"`\n\t}\n\tresult := make([]apiProject, len(projects))\n\tfor i, dir := range projects {\n\t\truns, _ := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n\t\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\n\t\tfor j, rr := range runs {\n\t\t\trunValues[j] = *rr\n\t\t}\n\t\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\n\t\tvar activeCount int\n\t\tfor _, rr := range runs {\n\t\t\tif rr.State == domain.RunStatePending || rr.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n\t\t\t\tactiveCount++\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\tresult[i] = apiProject{\n\t\t\tDir:   dir,\n\t\t\tLabel: labels[dir],\n\t\t\tHealth: apiHealth{\n\t\t\t\tStatus: string(health.Status),\n\t\t\t\tPassed: health.Passed,\n\t\t\t\tFailed: health.Failed,\n\t\t\t\tTotal:  health.Total,\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tActiveCount: activeCount,\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(result)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIRunDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tcaps, err := h.captures.GetCaptures(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tcaps = nil\n\t}\n\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\tmerged := mergeCaptures(caps)\n\tsteps := make([]apiStep, len(merged))\n\tfor i, e := range merged {\n\t\tsteps[i] = apiStep{\n\t\t\tStepName:  e.StepName,\n\t\t\tResult:    e.Result,\n\t\t\tStartedAt: formatTime(e.StartedAt),\n\t\t\tDuration:  e.Duration,\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Fetch child runs for the API response\n\tvar apiChildren []apiRun\n\tif children, err := h.store.ListChildRuns(r.Context(), id); err == nil {\n\t\tfor _, c := range children {\n\t\t\tapiChildren = append(apiChildren, toAPIRun(c, labels))\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tdetail := apiRunDetail{\n\t\tapiRun:         toAPIRun(run, labels),\n\t\tContainerState: h.containerState(r.Context(), run),\n\t\tSteps:          steps,\n\t\tChildRuns:      apiChildren,\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(detail)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIStepOutput(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\tstep := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n\tlogType := r.URL.Query().Get(\"type\")   // optional: \"script\", \"llm\"\n\tformat := r.URL.Query().Get(\"format\")  // optional: \"raw\" to skip parsing\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\twriteOutput := func(data []byte) {\n\t\tif format != \"raw\" {\n\t\t\tdata = logstream.ParseClaudeStream(data)\n\t\t}\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\t\tw.Write(data)\n\t}\n\n\t// Try log index first for fast lookup\n\tif h.logStore != nil {\n\t\tlogFiles, err := h.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(r.Context(), id, step)\n\t\tif err == nil && len(logFiles) > 0 {\n\t\t\t// If type filter specified, narrow results\n\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n\t\t\t\tif logType != \"\" && lf.FileType != logType {\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tdata, readErr := os.ReadFile(lf.FilePath)\n\t\t\t\tif readErr == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\t\t\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\toutputDir := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", id, \"output\")\n\n\t// Fall back to file path conventions\n\t// If type is \"llm\", try llm-<step>.log\n\tif logType == \"llm\" {\n\t\tllmPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, \"llm-\"+step+\".log\")\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(llmPath)\n\t\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Try per-step output file\n\toutputPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, step+\".log\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath)\n\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Do NOT fall back to container.log or live docker logs here — those\n\t// contain unfiltered output from ALL steps and would show the wrong\n\t// content for this specific step (the root cause of web-UI log mismatches).\n\n\thttp.Error(w, \"step output not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIStopRun(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run not found\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Only allow stopping active runs\n\tif run.State != domain.RunStatePending && run.State != domain.RunStateRunning {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run is not active\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n\tif !ok || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tif err := mgr.Stop(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to stop run: %v\", err)})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateCancelled)\n\tif err := h.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run); err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to update run: %v\", err)})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIDeleteContainer(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run not found\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n\tif !ok || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tif err := mgr.Remove(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to remove container: %v\", err)})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\trun.ContainerKept = false\n\tif err := h.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run); err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to update run: %v\", err)})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n}\n\n// handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers mass-deletes all retained/exited containers for a project.\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\truns, err := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"failed to list runs\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tvar deleted int\n\tvar errors []string\n\tfor _, run := range runs {\n\t\tif !run.ContainerKept || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Check container is not running\n\t\tstatus, err := mgr.Inspect(r.Context(), run.ContainerID)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t// Container already gone — just clear the flag\n\t\t\trun.ContainerKept = false\n\t\t\th.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run)\n\t\t\tdeleted++\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tif status.Running {\n\t\t\tcontinue // skip running containers\n\t\t}\n\t\tif err := mgr.Remove(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); err != nil {\n\t\t\terrors = append(errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", run.ID, err))\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\trun.ContainerKept = false\n\t\tif err := h.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run); err != nil {\n\t\t\terrors = append(errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: update failed: %v\", run.ID, err))\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tdeleted++\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tresp := map[string]any{\"deleted\": deleted}\n\tif len(errors) > 0 {\n\t\tresp[\"errors\"] = errors\n\t}\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n}\n\n// handleAPIStream serves an SSE stream of log lines for a run.\n// For active runs, it subscribes to the live broadcaster.\n// For completed runs, it serves the archived full.log then closes.\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIStream(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tflusher, ok := w.(http.Flusher)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"streaming not supported\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/event-stream\")\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Cache-Control\", \"no-cache\")\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Connection\", \"keep-alive\")\n\tw.Header().Set(\"X-Accel-Buffering\", \"no\")\n\n\tisComplete := run.State == domain.RunStateSucceeded ||\n\t\trun.State == domain.RunStateFailed ||\n\t\trun.State == domain.RunStateCancelled\n\n\tif isComplete {\n\t\t// Serve archived full.log\n\t\th.streamFullLog(w, flusher, run)\n\t\t// Send done event\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"event: done\\ndata: %s\\n\\n\", string(run.State))\n\t\tflusher.Flush()\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Active run: subscribe to live broadcaster\n\tif h.logBroadcast == nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"log streaming not available\", http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tsub := h.logBroadcast.Subscribe(id)\n\tdefer h.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(id, sub)\n\n\tctx := r.Context()\n\tfor {\n\t\tselect {\n\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n\t\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\t\t// Stream finished (run completed)\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"event: done\\ndata: completed\\n\\n\")\n\t\t\t\tflusher.Flush()\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tline = parseLLMLogLine(line)\n\t\t\tif line.Type == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue // skip protocol-only llm lines\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(line)\n\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"data: %s\\n\\n\", data)\n\t\t\tflusher.Flush()\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\n// logLineRegex parses \"[timestamp] [type] content\" format from full.log.\nvar logLineRegex = regexp.MustCompile(`^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`)\n\n// streamFullLog reads the archived full.log file and sends its entries as SSE events.\n// LLM-type lines are parsed from raw Claude JSON into human-readable text.\nfunc (h *Handler) streamFullLog(w http.ResponseWriter, flusher http.Flusher, run *domain.Run) {\n\tlogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", run.ID, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n\tf, err := os.Open(logPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tdefer f.Close()\n\n\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(f)\n\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n\t\ttext := scanner.Text()\n\t\tline := parseFullLogLine(text)\n\t\tline = parseLLMLogLine(line)\n\t\tif line.Type == \"\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue // skip protocol-only llm lines\n\t\t}\n\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(line)\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"data: %s\\n\\n\", data)\n\t\tflusher.Flush()\n\t}\n}\n\n// parseLLMLogLine parses a LogLine whose type is \"llm\". If the content is\n// Claude stream JSON, it extracts the human-readable text. Protocol-only\n// events return a LogLine with an empty Type (caller should skip it).\n// Non-llm lines are returned unchanged.\nfunc parseLLMLogLine(line logstream.LogLine) logstream.LogLine {\n\tif line.Type != \"llm\" {\n\t\treturn line\n\t}\n\ttext, ok := logstream.ParseClaudeLine([]byte(line.Content))\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{} // signal to skip\n\t}\n\tline.Content = text\n\treturn line\n}\n\n// parseFullLogLine parses a \"[timestamp] [type] content\" line into a LogLine.\nfunc parseFullLogLine(text string) logstream.LogLine {\n\tm := logLineRegex.FindStringSubmatch(text)\n\tif m == nil {\n\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n\t\t\tTimestamp: time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339),\n\t\t\tType:      \"script\",\n\t\t\tContent:   text,\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n\t\tTimestamp: m[1],\n\t\tType:      m[2],\n\t\tContent:   m[3],\n\t}\n}\n\n// --- Project detail handlers ---\n\n// resolveProjectDir resolves a project label from the URL to its directory path.\n// Returns (dir, label, ok). Writes a JSON error response if not found.\nfunc (h *Handler) resolveProjectDir(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) (string, string, bool) {\n\tlabel := r.PathValue(\"name\")\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\tfor dir, l := range labels {\n\t\tif l == label {\n\t\t\treturn dir, label, true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"project not found\"})\n\treturn \"\", \"\", false\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleProjectDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, label, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\truns, _ := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n\tn := 10\n\tif n > len(runs) {\n\t\tn = len(runs)\n\t}\n\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\n\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n\t\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{ID: runs[i].ID, State: string(runs[i].State)}\n\t}\n\n\tvar containerCount int\n\tfor _, run := range runs {\n\t\tif run.ContainerKept {\n\t\t\tcontainerCount++\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tdata := map[string]any{\n\t\t\"Title\":          label,\n\t\t\"Label\":          label,\n\t\t\"Dir\":            dir,\n\t\t\"RecentRuns\":     dots,\n\t\t\"ContainerCount\": containerCount,\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\tif err := h.pages[\"project_detail\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIProjectInfo(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Docker image: read FROM line from Dockerfile\n\tdockerImage := \"\"\n\tdockerfilePath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"Dockerfile\")\n\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(dockerfilePath); err == nil {\n\t\t// Find the last FROM line (final stage)\n\t\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(string(data), \"\\n\") {\n\t\t\ttrimmed := strings.TrimSpace(line)\n\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(strings.ToUpper(trimmed), \"FROM \") {\n\t\t\t\tparts := strings.Fields(trimmed)\n\t\t\t\tif len(parts) >= 2 {\n\t\t\t\t\tdockerImage = parts[1]\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Version\n\tversion := 0\n\tversionPath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"version\")\n\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(versionPath); err == nil {\n\t\tif v, err := strconv.Atoi(strings.TrimSpace(string(data))); err == nil {\n\t\t\tversion = v\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Prompt files history\n\ttype commitEntry struct {\n\t\tSHA     string `json:\"sha\"`\n\t\tDate    string `json:\"date\"`\n\t\tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n\t}\n\ttype promptFile struct {\n\t\tPath    string        `json:\"path\"`\n\t\tHistory []commitEntry `json:\"history\"`\n\t}\n\n\tvar promptFiles []promptFile\n\tpromptsDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"prompts\")\n\tif entries, err := os.ReadDir(promptsDir); err == nil {\n\t\tfor _, e := range entries {\n\t\t\tif e.IsDir() {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\trelPath := filepath.Join(\".cloche\", \"prompts\", e.Name())\n\t\t\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"log\", \"--follow\", \"--format=%H %aI %s\", \"--\", relPath)\n\t\t\tcmd.Dir = dir\n\t\t\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tvar history []commitEntry\n\t\t\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(strings.TrimSpace(string(out)), \"\\n\") {\n\t\t\t\tif line == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tparts := strings.SplitN(line, \" \", 3)\n\t\t\t\tif len(parts) < 3 {\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t// Parse date to short form\n\t\t\t\tdateStr := parts[1]\n\t\t\t\tif t, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, dateStr); err == nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tdateStr = t.Format(\"2006-01-02\")\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\thistory = append(history, commitEntry{\n\t\t\t\t\tSHA:     parts[0][:7],\n\t\t\t\t\tDate:    dateStr,\n\t\t\t\t\tMessage: parts[2],\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tpromptFiles = append(promptFiles, promptFile{Path: relPath, History: history})\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]any{\n\t\t\"docker_image\": dockerImage,\n\t\t\"version\":      version,\n\t\t\"prompt_files\": promptFiles,\n\t})\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIPromptDiff(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tfile := r.URL.Query().Get(\"file\")\n\tsha := r.URL.Query().Get(\"sha\")\n\tif file == \"\" || sha == \"\" {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"file and sha required\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Validate sha is alphanumeric to prevent injection\n\tfor _, c := range sha {\n\t\tif !((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')) {\n\t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"invalid sha\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n\tcmd.Dir = dir\n\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"diff not available\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\tw.Write(out)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIWorkflows(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode([]any{})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\ttype apiWire struct {\n\t\tFrom   string `json:\"from\"`\n\t\tResult string `json:\"result\"`\n\t\tTo     string `json:\"to\"`\n\t}\n\ttype apiStepDef struct {\n\t\tName    string            `json:\"name\"`\n\t\tType    string            `json:\"type\"`\n\t\tResults []string          `json:\"results\"`\n\t\tConfig  map[string]string `json:\"config\"`\n\t}\n\ttype apiWorkflow struct {\n\t\tName      string       `json:\"name\"`\n\t\tFile      string       `json:\"file\"`\n\t\tSteps     []apiStepDef `json:\"steps\"`\n\t\tWires     []apiWire    `json:\"wires\"`\n\t\tEntryStep string       `json:\"entry_step\"`\n\t}\n\n\tvar workflows []apiWorkflow\n\tfor _, e := range entries {\n\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\twf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tvar steps []apiStepDef\n\t\tfor _, s := range wf.Steps {\n\t\t\tsteps = append(steps, apiStepDef{\n\t\t\t\tName:    s.Name,\n\t\t\t\tType:    string(s.Type),\n\t\t\t\tResults: s.Results,\n\t\t\t\tConfig:  s.Config,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Sort steps by name for consistent ordering\n\t\tsort.Slice(steps, func(i, j int) bool { return steps[i].Name < steps[j].Name })\n\n\t\tvar wires []apiWire\n\t\tfor _, wire := range wf.Wiring {\n\t\t\twires = append(wires, apiWire{From: wire.From, Result: wire.Result, To: wire.To})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tworkflows = append(workflows, apiWorkflow{\n\t\t\tName:      wf.Name,\n\t\t\tFile:      filepath.Join(\".cloche\", e.Name()),\n\t\t\tSteps:     steps,\n\t\t\tWires:     wires,\n\t\t\tEntryStep: wf.EntryStep,\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(workflows)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIStepContent(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tworkflowName := r.PathValue(\"workflow\")\n\tstepName := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n\n\t// Find the workflow file\n\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n\tvar wf *domain.Workflow\n\tentries, _ := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n\tfor _, e := range entries {\n\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tparsed, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tif parsed.Name == workflowName {\n\t\t\twf = parsed\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif wf == nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"workflow not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tstep, ok := wf.Steps[stepName]\n\tif !ok {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"step not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Try to read the referenced file from step config\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\n\tif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n\t\tcontent, err := resolveFileRef(prompt, dir)\n\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif cmd := step.Config[\"command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n\t\tcontent, _ := resolveFileRef(cmd, dir)\n\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif script := step.Config[\"script\"]; script != \"\" {\n\t\tcontent, _ := resolveFileRef(script, dir)\n\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\thttp.Error(w, \"no content available\", http.StatusNotFound)\n}\n\n// --- Template helpers ---\n\n// resolveFileRef resolves file(\"path\") DSL syntax to actual file contents.\n// If the value uses file() syntax, the referenced file is read from disk.\n// Otherwise the value is returned as-is.\nfunc resolveFileRef(value, baseDir string) (string, error) {\n\tif strings.HasPrefix(value, `file(\"`) && strings.HasSuffix(value, `\")`) {\n\t\tpath := value[6 : len(value)-2]\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(baseDir, path))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn string(data), nil\n\t}\n\treturn value, nil\n}\n\nfunc stateColor(state domain.RunState) string {\n\tswitch state {\n\tcase domain.RunStatePending:\n\t\treturn \"pending\"\n\tcase domain.RunStateRunning:\n\t\treturn \"running\"\n\tcase domain.RunStateSucceeded:\n\t\treturn \"succeeded\"\n\tcase domain.RunStateFailed:\n\t\treturn \"failed\"\n\tcase domain.RunStateCancelled:\n\t\treturn \"cancelled\"\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"pending\"\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc healthColor(status domain.HealthStatus) string {\n\tswitch status {\n\tcase domain.HealthGreen:\n\t\treturn \"green\"\n\tcase domain.HealthYellow:\n\t\treturn \"yellow\"\n\tcase domain.HealthRed:\n\t\treturn \"red\"\n\tcase domain.HealthBlue:\n\t\treturn \"blue\"\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"grey\"\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc formatTime(t time.Time) string {\n\tif t.IsZero() {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\treturn t.Format(\"2006-01-02 15:04:05\")\n}\n\nfunc formatDuration(start, end time.Time) string {\n\tif start.IsZero() || end.IsZero() {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\td := end.Sub(start)\n\tif d < time.Second {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dms\", d.Milliseconds())\n\t}\n\tif d < time.Minute {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%.1fs\", d.Seconds())\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dm%ds\", int(d.Minutes()), int(d.Seconds())%60)\n}\n\n// formatSmartDuration formats a duration into a human-friendly short string.\n// Examples: \"3s\", \"2m\", \"1h20m\", \"3h\".\nfunc formatSmartDuration(d time.Duration) string {\n\tif d < time.Minute {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%ds\", int(d.Seconds()))\n\t}\n\th := int(d.Hours())\n\tm := int(d.Minutes()) % 60\n\tif h == 0 {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dm\", m)\n\t}\n\tif m == 0 {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dh\", h)\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dh%dm\", h, m)\n}\n\n// roundRelativeTime rounds a duration to neat display units:\n// <1m -> \"<1m ago\", then 1m,5m,10m,15m,30m,45m,1h,2h,3h,...24h,\n// then days.\nfunc roundRelativeTime(d time.Duration) string {\n\tif d < time.Minute {\n\t\treturn \"<1m ago\"\n\t}\n\tmins := int(d.Minutes())\n\thours := int(d.Hours())\n\tdays := hours / 24\n\n\tif days > 0 {\n\t\tif days == 1 {\n\t\t\treturn \"1 day ago\"\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%d days ago\", days)\n\t}\n\tif hours >= 1 {\n\t\tif hours == 1 {\n\t\t\treturn \"1 hour ago\"\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%d hours ago\", hours)\n\t}\n\t// Round minutes to neat breakpoints\n\tswitch {\n\tcase mins < 3:\n\t\treturn \"1m ago\"\n\tcase mins < 8:\n\t\treturn \"5m ago\"\n\tcase mins < 13:\n\t\treturn \"10m ago\"\n\tcase mins < 20:\n\t\treturn \"15m ago\"\n\tcase mins < 38:\n\t\treturn \"30m ago\"\n\tcase mins < 53:\n\t\treturn \"45m ago\"\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"1 hour ago\"\n\t}\n}\n\n// formatRunTiming returns a smart timing string for display on the Runs page.\n// Running: \"5m\" (just duration so far)\n// Completed: \"20m, 1 hour ago\"\n// Pending: \"\"\nfunc formatRunTiming(state domain.RunState, startedAt, completedAt time.Time) string {\n\treturn formatRunTimingAt(state, startedAt, completedAt, time.Now())\n}\n\n// formatRunTimingAt is the testable version of formatRunTiming with an explicit \"now\".\nfunc formatRunTimingAt(state domain.RunState, startedAt, completedAt, now time.Time) string {\n\tif startedAt.IsZero() {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\tswitch state {\n\tcase domain.RunStateRunning:\n\t\td := now.Sub(startedAt)\n\t\treturn formatSmartDuration(d)\n\tdefault:\n\t\tif completedAt.IsZero() {\n\t\t\treturn \"\"\n\t\t}\n\t\td := completedAt.Sub(startedAt)\n\t\tago := now.Sub(completedAt)\n\t\treturn formatSmartDuration(d) + \", \" + roundRelativeTime(ago)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc truncate(s string, n int) string {\n\tif len(s) <= n {\n\t\treturn s\n\t}\n\treturn s[:n] + \"...\"\n}\n\nfunc shortContainerID(id string) string {\n\tif len(id) > 12 {\n\t\treturn id[:12]\n\t}\n\treturn id\n}\n\n// projectLabels builds a mapping from full project directory paths to short\n// display labels. Each label is the final directory component (e.g.\n// \"myproject\" from \"/home/user/workspace/myproject\"). When two projects share\n// the same final name, the parent directory is prepended to disambiguate\n// (e.g. \"foo/bar\" vs \"baz/bar\").\nfunc projectLabels(dirs []string) map[string]string {\n\tlabels := make(map[string]string, len(dirs))\n\t// Group dirs by their base name to detect conflicts.\n\tbyBase := map[string][]string{}\n\tfor _, d := range dirs {\n\t\tbase := filepath.Base(d)\n\t\tbyBase[base] = append(byBase[base], d)\n\t}\n\tfor base, paths := range byBase {\n\t\tif len(paths) == 1 {\n\t\t\tlabels[paths[0]] = base\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tfor _, p := range paths {\n\t\t\t\tparent := filepath.Base(filepath.Dir(p))\n\t\t\t\tlabels[p] = parent + \"/\" + base\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn labels\n}\n\ntype projectEntry struct {\n\tDir            string\n\tLabel          string\n\tContainerCount int\n}\n","numLines":1437,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1437}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017ytgPEaML4n7uFTWRJ2cec","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **Domain**: The `Task` type already exists in `internal/host/task.go`. I need to think about how to expose task information. The Loop struct manages tasks internally with a dedup map. I need to add the ability to query current tasks and their assignment state.\n\n2. **What information to expose**:\n   - List of tasks from the task pipeline (from list-tasks)\n   - Which tasks are assigned to which runs (from dedup map)\n   - Task assignment state (open, assigned/in-progress, completed)\n\n3. **Changes needed**:\n   - Add a method to the Loop to retrieve current task state with task-to-run-id mappings, not just task-to-time tracking\n   - Create a `ListTasks` RPC in the gRPC proto and implement it in the server\n   - Add a `cloche tasks` CLI command and a `/api/projects/{name}/tasks` web endpoint\n   - Write tests for the new functionality\n\nThe key design consideration is that the Loop's dedup map currently only tracks timing information, but I need to extend it to expose which run each task is assigned to.\n\nLooking at the task pipeline, list-tasks discovers tasks from an external source, the loop selects open non-deduped tasks, and assigns each to a run. To show upcoming tasks and their assignment state, I need to track task information and run associations within the Loop itself. I'll create a TaskInfo type that bundles the task with its assignment metadata like run ID and assignment time, then expose this through a getter method.\n\nSince the Loop fetches tasks asynchronously, I'll cache the last fetched set to avoid re-running list-tasks when external queries come in. The gRPC server can then add a ListTasks RPC that queries the loop for a specific project.\n\nAdding task state tracking to the domain layer...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6179,"cache_creation_input_tokens":40838,"cache_read_input_tokens":19721,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":40838},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6146b7bf-a511-4374-8899-2af97fce0332","uuid":"9579381d-c1b0-4a60-89d0-83b845f7c1fc"}
