{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016RLWgKtBZgFcFEpCLGAsAC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package host\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"fmt\"\n     6→\t\"log\"\n     7→\t\"os\"\n     8→\t\"path/filepath\"\n     9→\t\"strings\"\n    10→\n    11→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/agents/prompt\"\n    12→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    13→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n    14→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/engine\"\n    15→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    16→)\n    17→\n    18→// Ensure hostStatusHandler implements engine.StatusHandler.\n    19→var _ engine.StatusHandler = (*hostStatusHandler)(nil)\n    20→\n    21→// Runner executes a host workflow by parsing host.cloche and walking the step graph.\n    22→type Runner struct {\n    23→\tDispatcher RunDispatcher\n    24→\tStore      ports.RunStore\n    25→\tTaskID     string   // optional task ID assigned by the daemon loop\n    26→\tExtraEnv   []string // additional KEY=VALUE env vars passed to all steps\n    27→}\n    28→\n    29→// RunResult contains the outcome of a host workflow execution.\n    30→type RunResult struct {\n    31→\tRunID     string\n    32→\tState     domain.RunState\n    33→\tOutputDir string // path to the step output directory\n    34→}\n    35→\n    36→// Run parses .cloche/host.cloche from projectDir and executes the \"main\" workflow.\n    37→func (r *Runner) Run(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (*RunResult, error) {\n    38→\treturn r.RunWithID(ctx, projectDir, domain.GenerateRunID(\"main\"))\n    39→}\n    40→\n    41→// RunWithID is like Run but uses the provided run ID instead of generating one.\n    42→func (r *Runner) RunWithID(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, orchRunID string) (*RunResult, error) {\n    43→\treturn r.runNamedWorkflow(ctx, projectDir, \"main\", orchRunID)\n    44→}\n    45→\n    46→// RunNamed parses .cloche/host.cloche from projectDir and executes the workflow\n    47→// with the given name. The host.cloche file may contain multiple workflows (e.g.\n    48→// \"list-tasks\", \"main\", \"finalize\"). Returns an error if the named workflow is\n    49→// not found.\n    50→func (r *Runner) RunNamed(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, workflowName string) (*RunResult, error) {\n    51→\torchRunID := domain.GenerateRunID(workflowName)\n    52→\treturn r.runNamedWorkflow(ctx, projectDir, workflowName, orchRunID)\n    53→}\n    54→\n    55→// runNamedWorkflow is the internal implementation that runs a specific named\n    56→// workflow from host.cloche.\n    57→func (r *Runner) runNamedWorkflow(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, workflowName string, orchRunID string) (*RunResult, error) {\n    58→\thostPath := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", \"host.cloche\")\n    59→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(hostPath)\n    60→\tif err != nil {\n    61→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading host.cloche: %w\", err)\n    62→\t}\n    63→\n    64→\tworkflows, err := dsl.ParseAllForHost(string(data))\n    65→\tif err != nil {\n    66→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing host.cloche: %w\", err)\n    67→\t}\n    68→\n    69→\twf, ok := workflows[workflowName]\n    70→\tif !ok {\n    71→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"host.cloche has no workflow %q\", workflowName)\n    72→\t}\n    73→\n    74→\t// Create output directory for step outputs\n    75→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", orchRunID, \"output\")\n    76→\tif err := os.MkdirAll(outputDir, 0755); err != nil {\n    77→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating output dir: %w\", err)\n    78→\t}\n    79→\n    80→\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow: starting %q for project %s (run %s)\", wf.Name, projectDir, orchRunID)\n    81→\n    82→\t// Persist the host run in the store so it appears in list/status/logs.\n    83→\thostRun := domain.NewRun(orchRunID, wf.Name)\n    84→\thostRun.ProjectDir = projectDir\n    85→\thostRun.IsHost = true\n    86→\tif err := r.Store.CreateRun(ctx, hostRun); err != nil {\n    87→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating host run record: %w\", err)\n    88→\t}\n    89→\thostRun.Start()\n    90→\t_ = r.Store.UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun)\n    91→\n    92→\texecutor := &Executor{\n    93→\t\tProjectDir: projectDir,\n    94→\t\tMainDir:    MainWorktreeDir(projectDir),\n    95→\t\tDispatcher: r.Dispatcher,\n    96→\t\tStore:      r.Store,\n    97→\t\tOutputDir:  outputDir,\n    98→\t\tWires:      wf.Wiring,\n    99→\t\tHostRunID:  orchRunID,\n   100→\t\tTaskID:     r.TaskID,\n   101→\t\tExtraEnv:   r.ExtraEnv,\n   102→\t}\n   103→\n   104→\t// Configure agent from workflow-level host config\n   105→\tif cmd := wf.Config[\"host.agent_command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n   106→\t\texecutor.AgentCommands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n   107→\t}\n   108→\tif args := wf.Config[\"host.agent_args\"]; args != \"\" {\n   109→\t\texecutor.AgentArgs = strings.Fields(args)\n   110→\t}\n   111→\n   112→\teng := engine.New(executor)\n   113→\teng.SetStatusHandler(&hostStatusHandler{\n   114→\t\tprojectDir: projectDir,\n   115→\t\torchRunID:  orchRunID,\n   116→\t\tstore:      r.Store,\n   117→\t})\n   118→\n   119→\trun, runErr := eng.Run(ctx, wf)\n   120→\n   121→\tresult := &RunResult{\n   122→\t\tRunID:     orchRunID,\n   123→\t\tState:     domain.RunStateFailed,\n   124→\t\tOutputDir: outputDir,\n   125→\t}\n   126→\tif run != nil {\n   127→\t\tresult.State = run.State\n   128→\t}\n   129→\n   130→\t// Persist final state.\n   131→\thostRun, _ = r.Store.GetRun(ctx, orchRunID)\n   132→\tif hostRun != nil {\n   133→\t\tif runErr != nil {\n   134→\t\t\thostRun.Fail(runErr.Error())\n   135→\t\t} else {\n   136→\t\t\thostRun.Complete(result.State)\n   137→\t\t}\n   138→\t\thostRun.ActiveSteps = nil\n   139→\t\t_ = r.Store.UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun)\n   140→\t}\n   141→\n   142→\tif runErr != nil {\n   143→\t\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow: %q failed for %s: %v\", wf.Name, projectDir, runErr)\n   144→\t\treturn result, runErr\n   145→\t}\n   146→\n   147→\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow: %q completed for %s with state %s\", wf.Name, projectDir, run.State)\n   148→\treturn result, nil\n   149→}\n   150→\n   151→// hostStatusHandler logs host workflow step events and persists them to the store.\n   152→type hostStatusHandler struct {\n   153→\tprojectDir string\n   154→\torchRunID  string\n   155→\tstore      ports.RunStore\n   156→}\n   157→\n   158→func (h *hostStatusHandler) OnStepStart(_ *domain.Run, step *domain.Step) {\n   159→\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow [%s]: step %q started\", h.orchRunID, step.Name)\n   160→\tif h.store != nil {\n   161→\t\tif r, err := h.store.GetRun(context.Background(), h.orchRunID); err == nil {\n   162→\t\t\tr.RecordStepStart(step.Name)\n   163→\t\t\t_ = h.store.UpdateRun(context.Background(), r)\n   164→\t\t}\n   165→\t}\n   166→}\n   167→\n   168→func (h *hostStatusHandler) OnStepComplete(_ *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string) {\n   169→\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow [%s]: step %q completed with result %q\", h.orchRunID, step.Name, result)\n   170→\tif h.store != nil {\n   171→\t\tif r, err := h.store.GetRun(context.Background(), h.orchRunID); err == nil {\n   172→\t\t\tr.RecordStepComplete(step.Name, result)\n   173→\t\t\t_ = h.store.UpdateRun(context.Background(), r)\n   174→\t\t}\n   175→\t}\n   176→}\n   177→\n   178→func (h *hostStatusHandler) OnRunComplete(run *domain.Run) {\n   179→\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow [%s]: run completed with state %s\", h.orchRunID, run.State)\n   180→}\n   181→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6146b7bf-a511-4374-8899-2af97fce0332","uuid":"787301c9-875a-428e-b04f-fe8b4b5770fb","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/host/runner.go","content":"package host\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"log\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/agents/prompt\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/engine\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n)\n\n// Ensure hostStatusHandler implements engine.StatusHandler.\nvar _ engine.StatusHandler = (*hostStatusHandler)(nil)\n\n// Runner executes a host workflow by parsing host.cloche and walking the step graph.\ntype Runner struct {\n\tDispatcher RunDispatcher\n\tStore      ports.RunStore\n\tTaskID     string   // optional task ID assigned by the daemon loop\n\tExtraEnv   []string // additional KEY=VALUE env vars passed to all steps\n}\n\n// RunResult contains the outcome of a host workflow execution.\ntype RunResult struct {\n\tRunID     string\n\tState     domain.RunState\n\tOutputDir string // path to the step output directory\n}\n\n// Run parses .cloche/host.cloche from projectDir and executes the \"main\" workflow.\nfunc (r *Runner) Run(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (*RunResult, error) {\n\treturn r.RunWithID(ctx, projectDir, domain.GenerateRunID(\"main\"))\n}\n\n// RunWithID is like Run but uses the provided run ID instead of generating one.\nfunc (r *Runner) RunWithID(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, orchRunID string) (*RunResult, error) {\n\treturn r.runNamedWorkflow(ctx, projectDir, \"main\", orchRunID)\n}\n\n// RunNamed parses .cloche/host.cloche from projectDir and executes the workflow\n// with the given name. The host.cloche file may contain multiple workflows (e.g.\n// \"list-tasks\", \"main\", \"finalize\"). Returns an error if the named workflow is\n// not found.\nfunc (r *Runner) RunNamed(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, workflowName string) (*RunResult, error) {\n\torchRunID := domain.GenerateRunID(workflowName)\n\treturn r.runNamedWorkflow(ctx, projectDir, workflowName, orchRunID)\n}\n\n// runNamedWorkflow is the internal implementation that runs a specific named\n// workflow from host.cloche.\nfunc (r *Runner) runNamedWorkflow(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, workflowName string, orchRunID string) (*RunResult, error) {\n\thostPath := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", \"host.cloche\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(hostPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading host.cloche: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tworkflows, err := dsl.ParseAllForHost(string(data))\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing host.cloche: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\twf, ok := workflows[workflowName]\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"host.cloche has no workflow %q\", workflowName)\n\t}\n\n\t// Create output directory for step outputs\n\toutputDir := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", orchRunID, \"output\")\n\tif err := os.MkdirAll(outputDir, 0755); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating output dir: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow: starting %q for project %s (run %s)\", wf.Name, projectDir, orchRunID)\n\n\t// Persist the host run in the store so it appears in list/status/logs.\n\thostRun := domain.NewRun(orchRunID, wf.Name)\n\thostRun.ProjectDir = projectDir\n\thostRun.IsHost = true\n\tif err := r.Store.CreateRun(ctx, hostRun); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating host run record: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\thostRun.Start()\n\t_ = r.Store.UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun)\n\n\texecutor := &Executor{\n\t\tProjectDir: projectDir,\n\t\tMainDir:    MainWorktreeDir(projectDir),\n\t\tDispatcher: r.Dispatcher,\n\t\tStore:      r.Store,\n\t\tOutputDir:  outputDir,\n\t\tWires:      wf.Wiring,\n\t\tHostRunID:  orchRunID,\n\t\tTaskID:     r.TaskID,\n\t\tExtraEnv:   r.ExtraEnv,\n\t}\n\n\t// Configure agent from workflow-level host config\n\tif cmd := wf.Config[\"host.agent_command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n\t\texecutor.AgentCommands = prompt.ParseCommands(cmd)\n\t}\n\tif args := wf.Config[\"host.agent_args\"]; args != \"\" {\n\t\texecutor.AgentArgs = strings.Fields(args)\n\t}\n\n\teng := engine.New(executor)\n\teng.SetStatusHandler(&hostStatusHandler{\n\t\tprojectDir: projectDir,\n\t\torchRunID:  orchRunID,\n\t\tstore:      r.Store,\n\t})\n\n\trun, runErr := eng.Run(ctx, wf)\n\n\tresult := &RunResult{\n\t\tRunID:     orchRunID,\n\t\tState:     domain.RunStateFailed,\n\t\tOutputDir: outputDir,\n\t}\n\tif run != nil {\n\t\tresult.State = run.State\n\t}\n\n\t// Persist final state.\n\thostRun, _ = r.Store.GetRun(ctx, orchRunID)\n\tif hostRun != nil {\n\t\tif runErr != nil {\n\t\t\thostRun.Fail(runErr.Error())\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\thostRun.Complete(result.State)\n\t\t}\n\t\thostRun.ActiveSteps = nil\n\t\t_ = r.Store.UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun)\n\t}\n\n\tif runErr != nil {\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow: %q failed for %s: %v\", wf.Name, projectDir, runErr)\n\t\treturn result, runErr\n\t}\n\n\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow: %q completed for %s with state %s\", wf.Name, projectDir, run.State)\n\treturn result, nil\n}\n\n// hostStatusHandler logs host workflow step events and persists them to the store.\ntype hostStatusHandler struct {\n\tprojectDir string\n\torchRunID  string\n\tstore      ports.RunStore\n}\n\nfunc (h *hostStatusHandler) OnStepStart(_ *domain.Run, step *domain.Step) {\n\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow [%s]: step %q started\", h.orchRunID, step.Name)\n\tif h.store != nil {\n\t\tif r, err := h.store.GetRun(context.Background(), h.orchRunID); err == nil {\n\t\t\tr.RecordStepStart(step.Name)\n\t\t\t_ = h.store.UpdateRun(context.Background(), r)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (h *hostStatusHandler) OnStepComplete(_ *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string) {\n\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow [%s]: step %q completed with result %q\", h.orchRunID, step.Name, result)\n\tif h.store != nil {\n\t\tif r, err := h.store.GetRun(context.Background(), h.orchRunID); err == nil {\n\t\t\tr.RecordStepComplete(step.Name, result)\n\t\t\t_ = h.store.UpdateRun(context.Background(), r)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (h *hostStatusHandler) OnRunComplete(run *domain.Run) {\n\tlog.Printf(\"host workflow [%s]: run completed with state %s\", h.orchRunID, run.State)\n}\n","numLines":181,"startLine":1,"totalLines":181}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MyaUB3nFy3xMaMV4gbYLE1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. The Run domain type doesn't track task IDs. The Runner has a TaskID field, but it's not stored in the Run. So I can't easily cross-reference runs and tasks.\n\nLet me design the implementation:\n\n1. **Loop changes** - Add `lastTasks` (cached from last list-tasks call) and `assignments` (task ID -> assignment info including run ID)\n2. **TaskStateEntry** - Task + assignment state\n3. **GetTaskSnapshot()** - Return current tasks with assignment state\n4. **gRPC server** - Add `GetLoopTasks(projectDir)` method\n\n\n5. **Web handler** - Accept a `TaskProvider` interface, add API endpoint\n6. **CLI** - Add `tasks` command using HTTP API\n\nFor the task-to-run mapping, I'll modify `runPhased()` to capture the run ID when it returns from mainFn and store it in the Loop's assignments map. The core goal is showing available tasks from the last list-tasks call, which ones are currently assigned via the dedup map, and when they were assigned—I can cross-reference the dedup map with recent runs to get the run IDs if needed.\n\nI'll track this with a `lastTasks` field and an `assignments` map that stores task ID to assignment info including the assigned time and run ID. After mainFn returns in `runPhased()`, I'll update the assignment with the run ID through a `trackAssignment` method. Now I'm wondering how the CLI command should work without gRPC—looking at the existing patterns, most commands use gRPC but `cloche logs --follow` uses HTTP SSE, so I should follow that precedent.\n\nI'll add a `ListTasks` method to `ClocheServer` that the web handler can call through a `TaskProvider` interface, then have the CLI hit the web API via HTTP like the logs command does. Let me start implementing the Loop changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4803,"cache_read_input_tokens":89707,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4803},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6146b7bf-a511-4374-8899-2af97fce0332","uuid":"4f06f1ab-630d-4323-8499-cfb36d624354"}
